of Men -- Just finding out -- what puzzled us -- Without the lexicon!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d247\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhat would I give to see his face? I'd give -- I'd give my life -- of course -- But that is not enough! Stop just a minute -- let me think! I'd give my biggest Bobolink! That makes two -- Him -- and Life! You know who "June" is -- I'd give her -- Roses a day from Zanzibar -- And Lily tubes -- like Wells -- Bees -- by the furlong - Straits of Blue Navies of Butterflies -- sailed thro' -And dappled Cowslip Dells --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThen I have "shares" in Primrose "Banks" -- Daffodil Dowries -- spicy "Stocks" -- Dominions -- broad as Dew -- Bags of Doublons -- adventurous Bees Brought me -- from firmamental seas -- And Purple -- from Peru --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNow -- have I bought it -- "Shylock"? Say! Sign me the Bond! "I vow to pay To Her -- who pledges this -- One hour -- of her Sovereign's face"! Ecstatic Contract! Niggard Grace! My Kingdom's worth of Bliss!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d248\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhy -- do they shut Me out of Heaven? Did I sing -- too loud? But -- I can say a little "Minor" Timid as a Bird!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWouldn't the Angels try me -- Just -- once -- more -- Just -- see -- if I troubled them -- But don't -- shut the door!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOh, if I -- were the Gentleman In the "White Robe" -- And they -- were the little Hand -- that knocked -Could -- I -- forbid?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d249\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWild Nights -- Wild Nights! Were I with thee Wild Nights should be Our luxury!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFutile -- the Winds -- To a Heart in port -- Done with the Compass -- Done with the Chart!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dRowing in Eden -- Ah, the Sea! Might I but moor -- Tonight -- In Thee!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d250\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI shall keep singing! Birds will pass me On their way to Yellower Climes -- Each -- with a Robin's expectation -I -- with my Redbreast -- And my Rhymes --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLate -- when I take my place in summer -- But -- I shall bring a fuller tune -- Vespers -- are sweeter than Matins -- Signor -- Morning -- only the seed of Noon --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d251\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOver the fence -- Strawberries -- grow -- Over the fence -- I could climb -- if I tried, I know -- Berries are nice!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut -- if I stained my Apron -- God would certainly scold! Oh, dear, -- I guess if He were a Boy -- He'd -- climb -- if He could!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d252\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI can wade Grief -- Whole Pools of it -- I'm used to that -- But the least push of Joy Breaks up my feet -- And I tip -- drunken -- Let no Pebble -- smile -'Twas the New Liquor -- That was all!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dPower is only Pain -- Stranded, thro' Discipline, Till Weights -- will hang -Give Balm -- to Giants -- And they'll wilt, like Men -- Give Himmaleh -- They'll Carry -- Him!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d253\u13\'0d\u13\'0dYou see I cannot see -- your lifetime -- I must guess -- How many times it ache for me -- today -- Confess -- How many times for my far sake The brave eyes film -- But I guess guessing hurts -- Mine -- got so dim!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dToo vague -- the face - My own -- so patient -- covers -- Too far -- the strength - My timidness enfolds - Haunting the Heart -- Like her translated faces -- Teasing the want -- It -- only -- can suffice!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d254\u13\'0d\u13\'0d"Hope" is the thing with feathers -- That perches in the soul -- And sings the tune without the words -- And never stops -- at all --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd sweetest -- in the Gale -- is heard -- And sore must be the storm -- That could abash the little Bird That kept so many warm --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI've heard it in the chillest land -- And on the strangest Sea -- Yet, never, in Extremity, It asked a crumb -- of Me.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d255\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo die -- takes just a little while -- They say it doesn't hurt -- It's only fainter -- by degrees -- And then -- it's out of sight --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA darker Ribbon -- for a Day -- A Crape upon the Hat -- And then the pretty sunshine comes -- And helps us to forget -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe absent -- mystic -- creature -- That but for love of us -- Had gone to sleep -- that soundest time -- Without the weariness -\u13\'0d\u13\'0d256\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIf I'm lost -- now That I was found -- Shall still my transport be -- That once -- on me -- those Jasper Gates Blazed open -- suddenly --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThat in my awkward -- gazing -- face -- The Angels -- softly peered -- And touched me with their fleeces, Almost as if they cared -- I'm banished -- now -- you know it -How foreign that can be -- You'll know -- Sir -- when the Savior's face Turns so -- away from you -- 257\u13\'0d\u13\'0dDelight is as the flight -Or in the Ratio of it, As the Schools would say -- The Rainbow's way -- A Skein Flung colored, after Rain, Would suit as bright, Except that flight Were Aliment --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d"If it would last" I asked the East, When that Bent Stripe Struck up my childish Firmament -- And I, for glee, Took Rainbows, as the common way, And empty Skies The Eccentricity --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd so with Lives -- And so with Butterflies - Seen magic -- through the fright That they will cheat the sight -- And Dower latitudes far on -- Some sudden morn -- Our portion -- in the fashion -- Done --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d258\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThere's a certain Slant of light, Winter Afternoons -- That oppresses, like the Heft Of Cathedral Tunes --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHeavenly Hurt, it gives us -- We can find no scar, But internal difference, Where the Meanings, are --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNone may teach it -- Any -- 'Tis the Seal Despair -- An imperial affliction Sent us of the Air --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhen it comes, the Landscape listens -- Shadows -- hold their breath -- When it goes, 'tis like the Distance On the look of Death --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d259\u13\'0d\u13\'0dGood Night! Which put the Candle out? A jealous Zephyr -- not a doubt -- Ah, friend, you little knew How long at that celestial wick The Angels -- labored diligent -- Extinguished -- now -- for you!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt might -- have been the Light House spark -- Some Sailor -- rowing in the Dark -- Had importuned to see! It might -- have been the waning lamp That lit the Drummer from the Camp To purer Reveille!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d260\u13\'0d\u13\'0dRead -- Sweet -- how others -- strove -- Till we -- are stouter -- What they -- renounced -- Till we -- are less afraid - How many times they -- bore the faithful witness -- Till we -- are helped -- As if a Kingdom -- cared!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dRead then -- of faith -- That shone above the fagot -- Clear strains of Hymn The River could not drown -- Brave names of Men -- And Celestial Women -- Passed out -- of Record Into -- Renown!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d261\u13\'0d\u13\'0dPut up my lute! What of -- my Music! Since the sole ear I cared to charm -- Passive -- as Granite -- laps My Music -- Sobbing -- will suit -- as well as psalm!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWould but the "Memnon" of the Desert -- Teach me the strain That vanquished Him -- When He -- surrendered to the Sunrise -- Maybe -- that -- would awaken -- them!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d262\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe lonesome for they know not What -- The Eastern Exiles -- be -- Who strayed beyond the Amber line Some madder Holiday --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd ever since -- the purple Moat They strive to climb -- in vain -- As Birds -- that tumble from the clouds Do fumble at the strain -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Blessed Ether -- taught them -- Some Transatlantic Morn -- When Heaven -- was too common -- to miss -- Too sure -- to dote upon! A single Screw of Flesh Is all that pins the Soul That stands for Deity, to Mine, Upon my side the Veil -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOnce witnessed of the Gauze -- Its name is put away As far from mine, as if no plight Had printed yesterday,\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIn tender -- solemn Alphabet, My eyes just turned to see, When it was smuggled by my sight Into Eternity --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMore Hands -- to hold -- These are but Two -- One more new-mailed Nerve Just granted, for the Peril's sake -- Some striding -- Giant -- Love --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSo greater than the Gods can show, They slink before the Clay, That not for all their Heaven can boast Will let its Keepsake -- go\u13\'0d\u13\'0d264\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Weight with Needles on the pounds -- To push, and pierce, besides -- That if the Flesh resist the Heft -- The puncture -- coolly tries --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThat not a pore be overlooked Of all this Compound Frame -- As manifold for Anguish -- As Species -- be -- for name -- Where Ships of Purple -- gently toss -- On Seas of Daffodil -- Fantastic Sailors -- mingle -- And then -- the Wharf is still!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d266\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThis -- is the land -- the Sunset washes -- These -- are the Banks of the Yellow Sea -- Where it rose -- or whither it rushes -These -- are the Western Mystery!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNight after Night Her purple traffic Strews the landing with Opal Bales -- Merchantmen -- poise upon Horizons -- Dip -- and vanish like Orioles!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d267\u13\'0d\u13\'0dDid we disobey Him? Just one time! Charged us to forget Him -- But we couldn't learn!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWere Himself -- such a Dunce -- What would we -- do? Love the dull lad -- best - Oh, wouldn't you?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d268\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMe, change! Me, alter! Then I will, when on the Everlasting Hill A Smaller Purple grows -- At sunset, or a lesser glow Flickers upon Cordillera -- At Day's superior close! Bound -- a trouble -- And lives can bear it! Limit -- how deep a bleeding go! So -- many -- drops -- of vital scarlet -- Deal with the soul As with Algebra!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTell it the Ages -- to a cypher -- And it will ache -- contented -- on -- Sing -- at its pain -- as any Workman -- Notching the fall of the Even Sun!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d270\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOne Life of so much Consequence! Yet I -- for it -- would pay -- My Soul's entire income -- In ceaseless -- salary --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOne Pearl -- to me -- so signal -- That I would instant dive -- Although -- I knew -- to take it -- Would cost me -- just a life!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Sea is full -- I know it! That -- does not blur my Gem! It burns -- distinct from all the row -- Intact -- in Diadem!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe life is thick -- I know it! Yet -- not so dense a crowd -- But Monarchs -- are perceptible -- Far down the dustiest Road! A solemn thing -- it was -- I said -- A woman -- white -- to be -- And wear -- if God should count me fit -- Her blameless mystery --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA hallowed thing -- to drop a life Into the purple well -- Too plummetless -- that it return -- Eternity -- until --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI pondered how the bliss would look -- And would it feel as big - When I could take it in my hand -- As hovering -- seen -- through fog --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd then -- the size of this "small" life -- The Sages -- call it small -- Swelled -- like Horizons -- in my vest -- And I sneered -- softly -- "small"!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d272\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI breathed enough to take the Trick -And now, removed from Air -- I simulate the Breath, so well -- That One, to be quite sure --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Lungs are stirless -- must}
