lish language -- I have heard but one -- Low as the laughter of the Cricket, Loud, as the Thunder's Tongue --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMurmuring, like old Caspian Choirs, When the Tide's a' lull -- Saying itself in new infection -- Like a Whippoorwill --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBreaking in bright Orthography On my simple sleep -- Thundering its Prospective -- Till I stir, and weep --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNot for the Sorrow, done me -- But the push of Joy -- Say it again, Saxton! Hush -- Only to me! 277\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhat if I say I shall not wait! What if I burst the fleshly Gate -- And pass escaped -- to thee!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhat if I file this Mortal -- off -- See where it hurt me -- That's enough -- And wade in Liberty!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThey cannot take me -- any more! Dungeons can call -- and Guns implore Unmeaning -- now -- to me --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAs laughter -- was -- an hour ago -- Or Laces -- or a Travelling Show -- Or who died -- yesterday!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d278\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA shady friend -- for Torrid days -- Is easier to find -- Than one of higher temperature For Frigid -- hour of Mind --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Vane a little to the East -- Scares Muslin souls -- away -- If Broadcloth Hearts are firmer -- Than those of Organdy --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWho is to blame? The Weaver? Ah, the bewildering thread! The Tapestries of Paradise So notelessly -- are made!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d279 Tie the Strings to my Life, My Lord, Then, I am ready to go! Just a look at the Horses -- Rapid! That will do!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dPut me in on the firmest side -- So I shall never fall -- For we must ride to the Judgment -- And it's partly, down Hill --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut never I mind the steeper -- And never I mind the Sea -- Held fast in Everlasting Race -- By my own Choice, and Thee --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dGoodbye to the Life I used to live -- And the World I used to know -- And kiss the Hills, for me, just once -Then -- I am ready to go!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d280\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI felt a Funeral, in my Brain, And Mourners to and fro Kept treading -- treading -- till it seemed That Sense was breaking through --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd when they all were seated, A Service, like a Drum -- Kept beating -- beating -- till I thought My Mind was going numb --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd then I heard them lift a Box And creak across my Soul With those same Boots of Lead, again, Then Space -- began to toll,\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAs all the Heavens were a Bell, And Being, but an Ear, And I, and Silence, some strange Race Wrecked, solitary, here -- And then a Plank in Reason, broke, And I dropped down, and down -- And hit a World, at every plunge, And Finished knowing -- then --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d281\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Tis so appalling -- it exhilarates -- So over Horror, it half Captivates -- The Soul stares after it, secure -- A Sepulchre, fears frost, no more --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo scan a Ghost, is faint -- But grappling, conquers it -- How easy, Torment, now -- Suspense kept sawing so --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Truth, is Bald, and Cold -- But that will hold -- If any are not sure -- We show them -- prayer -- But we, who know, Stop hoping, now --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLooking at Death, is Dying -- Just let go the Breath -- And not the pillow at your Cheek So Slumbereth --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOthers, Can wrestle -- Yours, is done -- And so of Woe, bleak dreaded -- come, It sets the Fright at liberty -- And Terror's free -- Gay, Ghastly, Holiday!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d282\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHow noteless Men, and Pleiads, stand, Until a sudden sky Reveals the fact that One is rapt Forever from the Eye -- Members of the Invisible, Existing, while we stare, In Leagueless Opportunity, O'ertakenless, as the Air --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhy didn't we detain Them? The Heavens with a smile, Sweep by our disappointed Heads Without a syllable --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d283\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Mien to move a Queen -- Half Child -- Half Heroine -- An Orleans in the Eye That puts its manner by For humbler Company When none are near Even a Tear -- Its frequent Visitor --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Bonnet like a Duke -- And yet a Wren's Peruke Were not so shy Of Goer by -- And Hands -- so slight -- They would elate a Sprite With Merriment --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Voice that Alters -- Low And on the Ear can go Like Let of Snow -- Or shift supreme -- As tone of Realm On Subjects Diadem --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dToo small -- to fear -- Too distant -- to endear -- And so Men Compromise And just -- revere -- The Drop, that wrestles in the Sea -- Forgets her own locality -- As I -- toward Thee --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dShe knows herself an incense small -- Yet small -- she sighs -- if All -- is All -- How larger -- be?\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Ocean -- smiles -- at her Conceit -- But she, forgetting Amphitrite -- Pleads -- "Me"?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d285\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Robin's my Criterion for Tune -- Because I grow -- where Robins do -But, were I Cuckoo born -- I'd swear by him -- The ode familiar -- rules the Noon -- The Buttercup's, my Whim for Bloom -- Because, we're Orchard sprung -- But, were I Britain born, I'd Daisies spurn -- None but the Nut -- October fit -- Because, through dropping it, The Seasons flit -- I'm taught -- Without the Snow's Tableau Winter, were lie -- to me -- Because I see -- New Englandly -- The Queen, discerns like me -- Provincially --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d286\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThat after Horror -- that 'twas us -- That passed the mouldering Pier -- Just as the Granite Crumb let go -- Our Savior, by a Hair --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA second more, had dropped too deep For Fisherman to plumb -- The very profile of the Thought Puts Recollection numb --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe possibility -- to pass Without a Moment's Bell -- Into Conjecture's presence -- Is like a Face of Steel -- That suddenly looks into ours With a metallic grin -- The Cordiality of Death -- Who drills his Welcome in --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d287\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Clock stopped -- Not the Mantel's -- Geneva's farthest skill Can't put the puppet bowing -- That just now dangled still --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAn awe came on the Trinket! The Figures hunched, with pain -- Then quivered out of Decimals -- Into Degreeless Noon --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt will not stir for Doctors -- This Pendulum of snow -- This Shopman importunes it -- While cool -- concernless No --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNods from the Gilded pointers -- Nods from the Seconds slim -- Decades of Arrogance between The Dial life -- And Him -- I'm Nobody! Who are you? Are you -- Nobody -- Too? Then there's a pair of us! Don't tell! they'd advertise -- you know!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHow dreary -- to be -- Somebody! How public -- like a Frog -- To tell one's name -- the livelong June -- To an admiring Bog!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d289\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI know some lonely Houses off the Road A Robber'd like the look of -- Wooden barred, And Windows hanging low, Inviting to -- A Portico, Where two could creep - One -- hand the Tools - The other peep -- To make sure All's Asleep -- Old fashioned eyes -- Not easy to surprise!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHow orderly the Kitchen'd look, by night, With just a Clock -- But they could gag the Tick -- And Mice won't bark -- And so the Walls -- don't tell -- None -- will --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA pair of Spectacles ajar just stir -- An Almanac's aware -- Was it the Mat -- winked, Or a Nervous Star? The Moon -- slides down the stair, To see who's there!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThere's plunder -- where -- Tankard, or Spoon -- Earring -- or Stone -- A Watch -- Some Ancient Brooch To match the Grandmama -- Staid sleeping -- there --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dDay -- rattles -- too Stealth's -- slow -- The Sun has got as far As the third Sycamore -- Screams Chanticleer "Who's there"?\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd Echoes -- Trains away, Sneer -- "Where"! While the old Couple, just astir, Fancy the Sunrise -- left the door ajar!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d290\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOf Bronze -- and Blaze -The North -- Tonight -- So adequate -- it forms -- So preconcerted with itself -- So distant -- to alarms -- And Unconcern so sovereign To Universe, or me -- Infects my simple spirit With Taints of Majesty -- Till I take vaster attitudes -- And strut upon my stem -- Disdaining Men, and Oxygen, For Arrogance of them --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMy Splendors, are Menagerie -- But their Completeless Show Will entertain the Centuries When I, am long ago, An Island in dishonored Grass -- Whom none but Beetles -- know.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d291 How the old Mountains drip with Sunset How the Hemlocks burn -- How the Dun Brake is draped in Cinder By the Wizard Sun --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHow the old Steeples hand the Scarlet Till the Ball is full -- Have I the lip of the Flamingo That I dare to tell?\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThen, how the Fire ebbs like Billows -- Touching all the Grass With a departing -- Sapphire -- feature -- As a Duchess passed -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHow a small Dusk crawls on the Village Till the Houses blot And the odd Flambeau, no men carry Glimmer on the Street --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHow it is Night -- in Nest and Kennel -- And where was the Wood -- Just a Dome of Abyss is Bowing Into Solitude --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThese}
