en they let go the ignominy -- smiling -- And Shame went still -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dUnto guessed Crests, my moaning fancy, leads me, Worn fair By Heads rejected -- in the lower country -- Of honors there -- Such spirit makes her perpetual mention, That I -- grown bold -- Step martial -- at my Crucifixion -- As Trumpets -- rolled -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFeet, small as mine -- have marched in Revolution Firm to the Drum -- Hands -- not so stout -- hoisted them -- in witness -- When Speech went numb -- Let me not shame their sublime deportments -- Drilled bright -- Beckoning -- Etruscan invitation -- Toward Light --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d296\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOne Year ago -- jots what? God -- spell the word! I -- can't -- Was't Grace? Not that -- Was't Glory? That -- will do -- Spell slower -- Glory --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSuch Anniversary shall be -- Sometimes -- not often -- in Eternity -- When farther Parted, than the Common Woe -- Look -- feed upon each other's faces -- so -- In doubtful meal, if it be possible Their Banquet's true --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI tasted -- careless -- then -- I did not know the Wine Came once a World -- Did you? Oh, had you told me so -- This Thirst would blister -- easier -- now -- You said it hurt you -- most -- Mine -- was an Acorn's Breast -- And could not know how fondness grew In Shaggier Vest -- Perhaps -- I couldn't -- But, had you looked in - A Giant -- eye to eye with you, had been -- No Acorn -- then --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSo -- Twelve months ago -- We breathed -- Then dropped the Air -- Which bore it best? Was this -- the patientest -- Because it was a Child, you know -- And could not value -- Air?\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIf to be "Elder" -- mean most pain -- I'm old enough, today, I'm certain -- then -- As old as thee -- how soon? One -- Birthday more -- or Ten? Let me -- choose! Ah, Sir, None!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d297\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt's like the Light -- A fashionless Delight -It's like the Bee -- A dateless -- Melody --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt's like the Woods -- Private -- Like the Breeze -- Phraseless -- yet it stirs The proudest Trees --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt's like the Morning -- Best -- when it's done -And the Everlasting Clocks -- Chime -- Noon!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d298\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAlone, I cannot be -- For Hosts -- do visit me -- Recordless Company -- Who baffle Key --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThey have no Robes, nor Names -- No Almanacs -- nor Climes -- But general Homes Like Gnomes --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTheir Coming, may be known By Couriers within -- Their going -- is not -- For they've never gone -- 299\u13\'0d\u13\'0dYour Riches -- taught me -- Poverty. Myself -- a Millionaire In little Wealths, as Girls could boast Till broad as Buenos Ayre --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dYou drifted your Dominions -- A Different Peru -- And I esteemed All Poverty For Life's Estate with you --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOf Mines, I little know -- myself -- But just the names, of Gems -- The Colors of the Commonest -- And scarce of Diadems --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSo much, that did I meet the Queen -- Her Glory I should know -- But this, must be a different Wealth -To miss it -- beggars so -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI'm sure 'tis India -- all Day -- To those who look on You -- Without a stint -- without a blame, Might I -- but be the Jew --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI'm sure it is Golconda -- Beyond my power to deem -- To have a smile for Mine -- each Day, How better, than a Gem!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAt least, it solaces to know That there exists -- a Gold -- Altho' I prove it, just in time Its distance -- to behold --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIts far -- far Treasure to surmise -- And estimate the Pearl -- That slipped my simple fingers through -- While just a Girl at School.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dPoems No. 300-399\u13\'0d\u13\'0d300\u13\'0d\u13\'0d"Morning" -- means "Milking" -- to the Farmer -- Dawn -- to the Teneriffe -- Dice -- to the Maid -- Morning means just Risk -- to the Lover -- Just revelation -- to the Beloved --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dEpicures -- date a Breakfast -- by it -- Brides -- an Apocalypse -- Worlds -- a Flood -- Faint-going Lives -- Their Lapse from Sighing -- Faith -- The Experiment of Our Lord\u13\'0d\u13\'0d301\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI reason, Earth is short -And Anguish -- absolute -- And many hurt, But, what of that?\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI reason, we could die -The best Vitality Cannot excel Decay, But, what of that?\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI reason, that in Heaven -- Somehow, it will be even -- Some new Equation, given -- But, what of that?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d302\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLike Some Old fashioned Miracle When Summertime is done -- Seems Summer's Recollection And the Affairs of June As infinite Tradition As Cinderella's Bays -- Or Little John -- of Lincoln Green -- Or Blue Beard's Galleries --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHer Bees have a fictitious Hum -- Her Blossoms, like a Dream -- Elate us -- till we almost weep -- So plausible -- they seem --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHer Memories like Strains -- Review -- When Orchestra is dumb -- The Violin in Baize replaced -- And Ear -- and Heaven -- numb --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d303\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Soul selects her own Society -- Then -- shuts the Door -- To her divine Majority -- Present no more --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dUnmoved -- she notes the Chariots -- pausing -- At her low Gate -- Unmoved -- an Emperor be kneeling Upon her Mat --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI've known her -- from an ample nation -- Choose One -- Then -- close the Valves of her attention -- Like Stone -\u13\'0d\u13\'0d304\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Day came slow -- till Five o'clock -- Then sprang before the Hills Like Hindered Rubies -- or the Light A Sudden Musket -- spills -- The Purple could not keep the East -- The Sunrise shook abroad Like Breadths of Topaz -- packed a Night -- The Lady just unrolled -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Happy Winds -- their Timbrels took -- The Birds -- in docile Rows Arranged themselves around their Prince The Wind -- is Prince of Those --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Orchard sparkled like a Jew -How mighty 'twas -- to be A Guest in this stupendous place -The Parlor -- of the Day --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d305\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe difference between Despair And Fear -- is like the One Between the instant of a Wreck And when the Wreck has been --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Mind is smooth -- no Motion -- Contented as the Eye Upon the Forehead of a Bust -- That knows -- it cannot see --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d306\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Soul's Superior instants Occur to Her -- alone -- When friend -- and Earth's occasion Have infinite withdrawn --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOr She -- Herself -- ascended To too remote a Height For lower Recognition Than Her Omnipotent --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThis Mortal Abolition Is seldom -- but as fair As Apparition -- subject To Autocratic Air --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dEternity's disclosure To favorites -- a few -- Of the Colossal substance Of Immortality\u13\'0d\u13\'0d307\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe One who could repeat the Summer day -- Were greater than itself -- though He Minutest of Mankind should be --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd He -- could reproduce the Sun -- At period of going down -- The Lingering -- and the Stain -- I mean --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhen Orient have been outgrown And Occident -- become Unknown -- His Name -- remain --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d308\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI send Two Sunsets -- Day and I -- in competition ran -- I finished Two -- and several Stars -- While He -- was making One --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHis own was ampler -- but as I Was saying to a friend - Mine -- is the more convenient To Carry in the Hand --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d309 For largest Woman's Hearth I knew -- 'Tis little I can do -- And yet the largest Woman's Heart Could hold an Arrow -- too -- And so, instructed by my own, I tenderer, turn Me to.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d310\u13\'0d\u13\'0dGive little Anguish -- Lives will fret -- Give Avalanches -- And they'll slant -- Straighten -- look cautious for their Breath -- But make no syllable -- like Death -Who only shows the Marble Disc -- Sublimer sort -- than Speech --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d311\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt sifts from Leaden Sieves -- It powders all the Wood. It fills with Alabaster Wool The Wrinkles of the Road --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt makes an Even Face Of Mountain, and of Plain -- Unbroken Forehead from the East Unto the East again --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt reaches to the Fence -It wraps it Rail by Rail Till it is lost in Fleeces -It deals Celestial Vail\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo Stump, and Stack -- and Stem -- A Summer's empty Room -- Acres of Joints, where Harvests were, Recordless, but for them-- It Ruffles Wrists of Posts As Ankles of a Queen -- Then stills its Artisans -- like Ghosts -- Denying they have been --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d312\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHer -- "last Poems" -- Poets -- ended -- Silver -- perished -- with her Tongue -- Not on Record -- bubbled other, Flute -- or Woman -- So divine -- Not unto its Summer -- Morning Robin -- uttered Half the Tune -- Gushed too free for the Adoring -- From the Anglo-Florentine -- Late -- the Praise -- 'Tis dull -- conferring On the Head too High to Crown -- Diadem -- or Ducal Showing -- Be its Grave -- sufficient sign -- Nought -- that We -- No Poet's Kinsman -- Suffocate -- with easy woe -- What, and if, Ourself a Bridegroom -- Put Her down -- in Italy?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d313\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI}
