Thee -- Play it were a Humming Bird -- And just sipped -- me --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d335\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Tis not that Dying hurts us so -- 'Tis Living -- hurts us more -- But Dying -- is a different way -- A Kind behind the Door --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Southern Custom -- of the Bird -- That ere the Frosts are due -- Accepts a better Latitude -- We -- are the Birds -- that stay.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Shrivers round Farmers' doors -- For whose reluctant Crumb -- We stipulate -- till pitying Snows Persuade our Feathers Home.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d336\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe face I carry with me -- last -- When I go out of Time -- To take my Rank -- by -- in the West -- That face -- will just be thine --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI'll hand it to the Angel -- That -- Sir -- was my Degree -- In Kingdoms -- you have heard the Raised -- Refer to -- possibly.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHe'll take it -- scan it -- step aside -- Return -- with such a crown As Gabriel -- never capered at -- And beg me put it on -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd then -- he'll turn me round and round -- To an admiring sky -- As one that bore her Master's name -- Sufficient Royalty!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d337\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI know a place where Summer strives With such a practised Frost -- She -- each year -- leads her Daisies back -- Recording briefly -- "Lost" --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut when the South Wind stirs the Pools And struggles in the lanes -- Her Heart misgives Her, for Her Vow -- And she pours soft Refrains\u13\'0d\u13\'0dInto the lap of Adamant -- And spices -- and the Dew -- That stiffens quietly to Quartz -- Upon her Amber Shoe --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d338\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI know that He exists. Somewhere -- in Silence -- He has hid his rare life From our gross eyes.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Tis an instant's play. 'Tis a fond Ambush -- Just to make Bliss Earn her own surprise!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut -- should the play Prove piercing earnest -Should the glee -- glaze -- In Death's -- stiff -- stare --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWould not the fun Look too expensive! Would not the jest -- 