t if the Bird from journey far -- Confused by Sweets -- as Mortals -- are -- Forget the secret of His wing And perish -- but a Bough between -- Oh, Groping feet -- Oh Phantom Queen!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d347\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhen Night is almost done -- And Sunrise grows so near That we can touch the Spaces -- It's time to smooth the Hair --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd get the Dimples ready -- And wonder we could care For that old -- faded Midnight -- That frightened -- but an Hour --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d348\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI dreaded that first Robin, so, But He is mastered, now, I'm accustomed to Him grown, He hurts a little, though -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI thought If I could only live Till that first Shout got by -- Not all Pianos in the Woods Had power to mangle me --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI dared not meet the Daffodils -- For fear their Yellow Gown Would pierce me with a fashion So foreign to my own --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI wished the Grass would hurry -- So -- when 'twas time to see -- He'd be too tall, the tallest one Could stretch -- to look at me --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI could not bear the Bees should come, I wished they'd stay away In those dim countries where they go, What word had they, for me?\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThey're here, though; not a creature failed -- No Blossom stayed away In gentle deference to me -- The Queen of Calvary --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dEach one salutes me, as he goes, And I, my childish Plumes, Lift, in bereaved acknowledgment Of their unthinking Drums --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d349\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI had the Glory -- that will do -- An Honor, Thought can turn her to When lesser Fames invite -- With one long "Nay" -- Bliss' early shape Deforming -- Dwindling -- Gulfing up -- Time's possibility.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d350\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThey leave us with the Infinite. But He -- is not a man -- His fingers are the size of fists -- His fists, the size of men --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd whom he foundeth, with his Arm As Himmaleh, shall stand -- Gibraltar's Everlasting Shoe Poised lightly on his Hand, So trust him, Comra