u13\'0d\u13\'0d370\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHeaven is so far of the Mind That were the Mind dissolved -- The Site -- of it -- by Architect Could not again be proved --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Tis vast -- as our Capacity -- As fair -- as our idea -- To Him of adequate desire No further 'tis, than Here --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d371\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA precious -- mouldering pleasure -- 'tis -- To meet an Antique Book -- In just the Dress his Century wore -- A privilege -- I think --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHis venerable Hand to take -- And warming in our own -- A passage back -- or two -- to make -- To Times when he -- was young --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHis quaint opinions -- to inspect -- His thought to ascertain On Themes concern our mutual mind -- The Literature of Man --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhat interested Scholars -- most -- What Competitions ran - When Plato -- was a Certainty -- And Sophocles -- a Man --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhen Sappho -- was a living Girl -- And Beatrice wore The Gown that Dante -- deified -- Facts Centuries before\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHe traverses -- familiar - As One should come to Town -- And tell you all your Dreams -- were true -- He lived -- where Dreams were born --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHis presence is Enchantment -- You beg him not to go -- Old Volume shake their Vellum Heads And tantalize -- just so -\u13\'0d\u13\'0d372\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI know lives, I could miss Without a Misery -- Others -- whose instant's wanting -- Would be Eternity --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe last -- a scanty Number -- 'Twould scarcely fill a Two -- The first -- a Gnat's Horizon Could easily outgrow --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d373\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI'm saying every day "If I should be a Queen, tomorrow" -- I'd do this way -- And so I deck, a little,\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIf it be, I wake a Bourbon, None on me, bend supercilious -- With "This was she -- Begged in the Market place -- Yesterday."\u13\'0d\u13\'0dCourt is a stately place - I've heard men say -- So I loop my apron, against the Majesty With bright Pins of Buttercup -- That not too plain -- Rank -