elf, must come --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dPoems No. 500-599\u13\'0d\u13\'0d500\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWithin my Garden, rides a Bird Upon a single Wheel -- Whose spokes a dizzy Music make As 'twere a travelling Mill --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHe never stops, but slackens Above the Ripest Rose -Partakes without alighting And praises as he goes,\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTill every spice is tasted -- And then his Fairy Gig Reels in remoter atmospheres -- And I rejoin my Dog,\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd He and I, perplex us If positive, 'twere we -- Or bore the Garden in the Brain This Curiosity --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut He, the best Logician, Refers my clumsy eye -- To just vibrating Blossoms! An Exquisite Reply!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d501\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThis World is not Conclusion. A Species stands beyond -- Invisible, as Music -- But positive, as Sound -- It beckons, and it baffles -- Philosophy -- don't know -- And through a Riddle, at the last -- Sagacity, must go -- To guess it, puzzles scholars -- To gain it, Men have borne Contempt of Generations And Crucifixion, shown - Faith slips -- and laughs, and rallies -- Blushes, if any see -- Plucks at a twig of Evidence -- And asks a Vane, the way -- Much Gesture, from the Pulpit -- Strong Hallelujahs roll - Narcotics cannot still the Tooth That nibbles at the soul -\u13\'0d\u13\'0d502\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAt least -- to pray -- is left -- is left -Oh Jesus -- in the Air - I know not which thy chamber is -- I'm knocking -- everywhere --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThou settest Earthquake in the South -- And Maelstrom, in the Sea -- Say, Jesus Christ of Nazareth -- Hast thou no Arm for Me?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d503\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBetter -- than Music! For I -- who heard it -- I was used -- to the Birds -- before -This -- was different -- 'Twas Translation -- Of all tunes I knew -- and more --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Twasn't contained -- like other stanza -- No one could play it -- the second time -- But the Composer -- perfect Mozart -- Perish with him -- that Keyless Rhyme!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSo -- Children -- told how Brooks in Eden -- Bubbled a better -- Melody -- Quaintly infer -- Eve's great surrender -- Urging the feet -- that would -- not -- fly -- Children -- matured -- are wiser -- mostly -- Eden -- a legend -- dimly told -- Eve -- and the Anguish -- Grandame's story -- But -- I was telling a tune -- I heard --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNot such a strain -- the Church -- baptizes -- When the last Saint -- goes up the Aisles -- Not such a stanza splits the silence -- When the Redemption strikes her Bells --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLet me not spill -- its smallest cadence -- Humming -- for promise -- when alone -- Humming -- until my faint Rehearsal -- Drop into tune -- around the Throne --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d504\u13\'0d\u13\'0dYou know that Portrait in the Moon -- So tell me who 'tis like - The very Brow -- the stooping eyes -- A fog for -- Say -- Whose Sake?\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe very Pattern of the Cheek -- It varies -- in the Chin -- But -- Ishmael -- since we met -- 'tis long -- And fashions -- intervene --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhen Moon's at full -- 'Tis Thou -- I say -- My lips just hold the name -- When crescent -- Thou art worn -- I note -- But -- there -- the Golden Same --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd when -- Some Night -- Bold -- slashing Clouds Cut Thee away from Me -- That's easier -- than the other film That glazes Holiday --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d505 I would not paint -- a picture -- I'd rather be the One Its bright impossibility To dwell -- delicious -- on -- And wonder how the fingers feel Whose rare -- celestial -- stir -- Evokes so sweet a Torment -- Such sumptuous -- Despair --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI would not talk, like Cornets -- I'd rather be the One Raised softly to the Ceilings -- And out, and easy on -- Through Villages of Ether -- Myself endued Balloon By but a lip of Metal -- The pier to my Pontoon --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNor would I be a Poet -- It's finer -- own the Ear -- Enamored -- impotent -- content -- The License to revere, A privilege so awful What would the Dower be, Had I the Art to stun