e meet --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThey strive -- and yet delay -- They perish -- Do we die -- Or is this Death's Experiment -- Reversed -- in Victory?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d551\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThere is a Shame of Nobleness -- Confronting Sudden Pelf -- A finer Shame of Ecstasy -- Convicted of Itself --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA best Disgrace -- a Brave Man feels -- Acknowledged -- of the Brave -- One More -- "Ye Blessed" -- to be told -- But that's -- Behind the Grave --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d552\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAn ignorance a Sunset Confer upon the Eye -- Of Territory -- Color -- Circumference -- Decay -- Its Amber Revelation Exhilirate -- Debase -- Omnipotence' inspection Of Our inferior face --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd when the solemn features Confirm -- in Victory -- We start -- as if detected In Immortality --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d553\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOne Crucifixion is recorded -- only -- How many be Is not affirmed of Mathematics -- Or History -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOne Calvary -- exhibited to Stranger -- As many be As persons -- or Peninsulas -- Gethsemane --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIs but a Province -- in the Being's Centre -- Judea -- For Journey -- or Crusade's Achieving -- Too near --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOur Lord -- indeed -- made Compound Witness -And yet -- There's newer -- nearer Crucifixion Than That --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d554\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Black Berry -- wears a Thorn in his side -- But no Man heard Him cry -- He offers His Berry, just the same To Partridge -- and to Boy --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHe sometimes holds upon the Fence -- Or struggles to a Tree -- Or clasps a Rock, with both His Hands -- But not for Sympathy --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWe -- tell a Hurt -- to cool it -- This Mourner -- to the Sky A little further reaches -- instead -- Brave Black Berry --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d555\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTrust in the Unexpected -- By this -- was William Kidd Persuaded of the Buried Gold -- As One had testified --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThrough this -- the old Philosopher -His Talismanic Stone Discerned -- still withholden To effort undivine --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Twas this -- allured Columbus -- When Genoa -- withdrew Before an Apparition Baptized America --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Same -- afflicted Thomas -- When Deity assured 'Twas better -- the perceiving not -- Provided it believed --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d556\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Brain, within its Groove Runs evenly -- and true -- But let a Splinter swerve -- 'Twere easier for You --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo put a Current back - When Floods have slit the Hills -- And scooped a Turnpike for Themselves -- And trodden out the Mills --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d557\u13\'0d\u13\'0dShe hideth Her the last -- And is the first, to rise - Her Night doth hardly recompense The Closing of Her eyes --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dShe doth Her Purple Work -- And putteth Her away In low Apartments in the Sod - As worthily as We.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo imitate her life As impotent would be As make of Our imperfect Mints, The Julep -- of the Bee --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d558\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut little Carmine hath her face -- Of Emerald scant -- her Gown -- Her Beauty -- is the love she doth -Itself -- exhibit -- Mine --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d559\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt knew no Medicine -- It was not Sickness -- then -- Nor any need of Surgery -- And therefore -- 'twas not Pain --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt moved away the Cheeks -- A Dimple at a time -- And left the Profile -- plainer -- And in the place of Bloom It left the little Tint That never had a Name -- You've seen it on a Cast's face -- Was Paradise -- to blame --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIf momently ajar -- Temerity -- drew near -- And sickened -- ever afterward For Somewhat that it saw?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d560\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt knew no lapse, nor Diminuation -- But large -- serene -- Burned on -- until through Dissolution -- It failed from Men --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI could not deem these Planetary forces Annulled -- But suffered an Exchange of Territory -- Or World --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d561\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI measure every Grief I meet With narrow, probing, Eyes -- I wonder if It weighs like Mine -- Or has an Easier 