My Own --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d562\u13\'0d\u13\'0dConjecturing a Climate Of unsuspended Suns -- Adds poignancy to Winter -- The Shivering Fancy turns\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo a fictitious Country To palliate a Cold -- Not obviated of Degree -- Nor erased -- of Latitude --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d563\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI could not prove the Years had feet -- Yet confident they run Am I, from symptoms that are past And Series that are done --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI find my feet have further Goals -- I smile upon the Aims That felt so ample -- Yesterday -- Today's -- have vaster claims --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI do not doubt the self I was Was competent to me -- But something awkward in the fit -- Proves that -- outgrown -- I see --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d564\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMy period had come for Prayer -- No other Art -- would do -- My Tactics missed a rudiment -- Creator -- Was it you?\u13\'0d\u13\'0dGod grows above -- so those who pray Horizons -- must ascend -- And so I stepped upon the North To see this Curious Friend --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHis House was not -- no sign had He -- By Chimney -- nor by Door Could I infer his Residence -- Vast Prairies of Air\u13\'0d\u13\'0dUnbroken by a Settler -- Were all that I could see -- Infinitude -- Had'st Thou no Face That I might look on Thee?\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Silence condescended -- Creation stopped -- for Me -- But awed beyond my errand -- I worshipped -- did not "pray" --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d565\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOne Anguish -- in a Crowd -- A Minor thing -- it sounds -- And yet, unto the single Doe Attempted of the Hounds\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Tis Terror as consummate As Legions of Alarm Did leap, full flanked, upon the Host -- 'Tis Units -- make the Swarm --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Small Leech -- on the Vitals -- The sliver, in the Lung - The Bung out -- of an Artery -- Are scarce accounted -- Harms --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dYet might -- by relation To that Repealless thing -- A Being -- impotent to end -- When once it has begun --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d566\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Dying Tiger -- moaned for Drink -- I hunted all the Sand -- I caught the Dripping of a Rock And bore it in my Hand --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHis Mighty Balls -- in death were thick -- But searching -- I could see A Vision on the Retina Of Water -- and of me -- 'Twas not my blame -- who sped too slow -- 'Twas not his blame -- who died While I was reaching him -- But 'twas -- the fact that He was dead --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d567\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHe gave away his Life -To Us -- Gigantic Sum -- A trifle -- in his own esteem -- But magnified -- by Fame --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dUntil it burst the Hearts That fancied they could hold -- When swift it slipped its limit -- And on the Heavens -- unrolled --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Tis Ours -- to wince -- and weep -- And wonder -- and decay By Blossoms gradual process -- He chose -- Maturity --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd quickening -- as we sowed -- Just obviated Bud -- And when We turned to note the Growth -- Broke -- perfect -- from the Pod --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d568\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWe learned the Whole of Love -- The Alphabet -- the Words -- A Chapter -- then the mighty Book -- Then -- Revelation closed --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut in Each Other's eyes An Ignorance beheld - Diviner than the Childhood's -- And each to each, a Child -- Attempted to expound What Neither -- understood -- Alas, that Wisdom is so large -- And Truth -- so manifold!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d569\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI reckon -- when I count it all -- First -- Poets -- Then the Sun -- Then Summer -- Then the Heaven of God -- And then -- the List is done --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut, looking back -- the First so seems To Comprehend the Whole -- The Others look a needless Show -- So I write -- Poets -- All -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTheir Summer -- lasts a Solid Year -- They can afford a Sun The East -- would deem extravagant -- And if the Further Heaven --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBe Beautiful as they prepare For Those who worship Them -- It is too difficult a Grace -- To justify the Dream --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d570\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI could die -- to know -- 'Tis a trifling knowledge -- News-Boys salute the Door -- Carts -- joggle by -- Morning's bold face -- stares in the window -- Were but mine -- the Charter of the least Fly --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHouses hunch the House With their Brick Shoulders -- Coals -- from a Rolling Load -- rattle -- how -- near -- To the very Square -- His foot is passing -- Possibly, this moment -- While I -- dream -- Here -- 571\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMust be a Woe -- A loss or so -- To bend the eye Best Beauty's way --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut -- once aslant It notes Delight As difficult As Stalactite\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Common Bliss Were had for less -- The price -- is Even as the Grace --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOur lord -- thought no Extravagance To pay -- a Cross --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d572\u13\'0d\u13\'0dDelight -- becomes pictorial -- When viewed through Pain -- More fair -- because impossible Than any gain --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Mountain -- at a given distance -In Amber -- lies -- Approached -- the Amber flits -- a little -- And That's -- the Skies -\u13\'0d\u13\'0d573\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Test of Love -- is Death -- Our Lord -- "so loved" -- it saith -- What Largest Lover -- hath Another -- doth --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIf smaller Patience -- be -- Through less Infinity -- If Bravo, sometimes swerve -- Through fainter Nerve --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAccept its Most -- And overlook -- the Dust -- Last -- Least -- The Cross' -- Request --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d574\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMy first well Day -- since many ill -- I asked to go abroad, And take the Sunshine in my hands, And see the things in Pod --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA 'blossom just when I went in To take my Chance with pain -- Uncertain if myself, or He, Should prove the strongest One.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Summer deepened, while we strove -- She put some flowers away -- And Redder cheeked Ones -- in their stead -- A fond -- illusive way --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo cheat Herself, it seemed she tried -- As if before a child To fade -- Tomorrow -- Rainbows held The Sepulchre, could hide.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dShe dealt a fashion to the Nut -- She tied the Hoods to Seeds -- She dropped bright scraps of Tint, about -- And left Brazilian Threads\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOn every shoulder that she met -- Then both her Hands of Haze Put up -- to hide her parting Grace From our unfitted eyes.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMy loss, by sickness -- Was it Loss? Or that Ethereal Gain One earns by measuring the Grave -- Then -- measuring the Sun --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d575\u13\'0d\u13\'0d"Heaven" has different Signs -- to me -- Sometimes, I think that Noon Is but a symbol of the Place -- And when again, at Dawn,\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA mighty look runs round the World And settles in the Hills - An Awe if it should be like that Upon the Ignorance steals --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Orchard, when the Sun is on -The Triumph of the Birds When they together Victory make -- Some Carnivals of Clouds --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Rapture of a finished Day -- Returning to the West - All these -- remind us of the place That Men call "paradise" --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dItself be fairer -- we suppose -- But how Ourself, shall be Adorned, for a Superior Grace -- Not yet, our eyes can see --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d576\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI prayed, at first, a little Girl, Because they told me to -- But stopped, when qualified to guess How prayer would feel -- to me -- If I believed God looked around, Each time my Childish eye Fixed full, and steady, on his own In Childish honesty --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd told him what I'd like, today, And parts of his far plan That baffled me -- The mingled side Of his Divinity --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd often since, in Danger, I count the force 'twould be To have a God so strong as that To hold my life for me\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTill I could take the Balance That tips so frequent, now, It takes me all the while to poise -- And then -- it doesn't stay --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d577\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIf I may have it, when it's dead, I'll be contented -- so - If just as soon as Breath is out It shall belong to me --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dUntil they lock it in the Grave, 'Tis Bliss I cannot weigh -- For tho' they lock Thee in the Grave, Myself -- can own the key --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThink of it Lover! I and Thee Permitted -- face to face to be -- After a Life -- a Death -- We'll say -- For Death was That -- And this -- is Thee --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI'll tell Thee All -- how Bald it grew -- How Midnight felt, at first -- to me -- How all the Clocks stopped in the World -- And Sunshine pinched me -- 'Twas so cold -- Then how the Grief got sleepy -- some -- As if my Soul were deaf and dumb -- Just making signs -- across -- to Thee -- That this way -- thou could'st notice me --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI'll tell you how I tried to keep A smile, to show you, when this Deep All Waded -- We look back for Play, At those Old Times -- in Calvary,\u13\'0d\u13\'0dForgive me, if the Grave come slow -- For Coveting to look at Thee -- Forgive me, if to stroke thy frost Outvisions Paradise!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d578\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Body grows without -- The more convenient way -- That if the Spirit -- like to hide Its Temple stands, alway,\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAjar -- secure -- inviting -- It never did betray The Soul that asked its shelter In solemn honesty\u13\'0d\u13\'0d579\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI had been hungry, all the Years -- My Noon had Come -- to dine -- I trembling drew the Table near -- And touched the Curious Wine --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Twas this on Tables I had seen -- When turning, hungry, Home I looked in Windows, for the Wealth I could not hope -- for Mine --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI did not know the ample Bread -- 'Twas so unlike the Crumb The Birds and I, had often shared In Nature's -- Dining Room --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Plenty hurt me -- 'twas so new -- Myself felt ill -- and odd -- As Berry -- of a Mountain Bush -- Transplanted -- to a Road --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNor was I hungry -- so I found That Hunger -- was a way Of Persons outside Windows -- The Entering -- takes away --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d580\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI gave myself to Him -- And took Himself, for Pay, The solemn contract of a Life Was ratified, this way --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Wealth might disappoint -- Myself a poorer prove Than this great Purchaser suspect, The Daily Own -- of Love\u13\'0d\u13\'0dDepreciate the Vision - But till the Merchant buy -- Still Fable -- in the Isles of Spice -- The subtle Cargoes -- lie --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAt least -- 'tis Mutual -- Risk -- Some -- found it -- Mutual Gain -- Sweet Debt of Life -- Each Night to owe -- Insolvent -- every Noon --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d581\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI found the words to every thought I ever had -- but One -- And that -- defies me -- As a Hand did try to chalk the Sun\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo Races -- nurtured in the Dark -- How would your own -- begin? Can Blaze be shown in Cochineal -Or Noon -- in Mazarin?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d582\u13\'0d\u13\'0dInconceivably solemn! Things go gay Pierce -- by the very Press Of Imagery --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTheir far Parades -- order on the eye With a mute Pomp -- A pleading Pageantry --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFlags, are a brave sight -- But no true Eye Ever went by One -- Steadily --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMusic's triumphant -- But the fine Ear Winces with delight Are Drums too near --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d583\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Toad, can die of Light -- Death is the Common Right Of Toads and Men -- Of Earl and Midge The privilege -- Why swagger,}
