then? The Gnat's supremacy is large as Thine --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLife -- is a different Thing -- So measure Wine -- Naked of Flask -- Naked of Cask -Bare Rhine -- Which Ruby's mine?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d584\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt ceased to hurt me, though so slow I could not feel the Anguish go -- But only knew by looking back -- That something -- had benumbed the Track --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNor when it altered, I could say, For I had worn it, every day, As constant as the Childish frock -- I hung upon the Peg, at night.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut not the Grief -- that nestled close As needles -- ladies softly press To Cushions Cheeks - To keep their place --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNor what consoled it, I could trace -Except, whereas 'twas Wilderness -It's better -- almost Peace --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d585\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI like to see it lap the Miles -- And lick the Valleys up -- And stop to feed itself at Tanks -- And then -- prodigious step\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAround a Pile of Mountains -- And supercilious peer In Shanties -- by the sides of Roads -- And then a Quarry pare\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo fit its Ribs And crawl between Complaining all the while In horrid -- hooting stanza -- Then chase itself down Hill --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd neigh like Boanerges -- Then -- punctual as a Star Stop -- docile and omnipotent At its own stable door -\u13\'0d\u13\'0d586\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWe talked as Girls do - Fond, and late -- We speculated fair, on every subject, but the Grave -- Of ours, none affair --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWe handled Destinies, as cool -- As we -- Disposers -- be -- And God, a Quiet Party To our Authority --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut fondest, dwelt upon Ourself As we eventual -- be -- When Girls to Women, softly raised We -- occupy -- Degree --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWe parted with a contract To cherish, and to write But Heaven made both, impossible Before another night.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d587\u13\'0d\u13\'0dEmpty my Heart, of Thee -- Its single Artery -- Begin, and leave Thee out -- Simply Extinction's Date --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMuch Billow hath the Sea -- One Baltic -- They -- Subtract Thyself, in play, And not enough of me Is left -- to put away -- "Myself" meanth Thee --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dErase the Root -- no Tree -- Thee -- then -- no me -- The Heavens stripped - Eternity's vast pocket, picked --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d588\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI cried at Pity -- not at Pain -- I heard a Woman say "Poor Child" -- and something in her voice Convicted me -- of me --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSo long I fainted, to myself It seemed the common way, And Health, and Laughter, Curious things -- To look at, like a Toy --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo sometimes hear "Rich people" buy And see the Parcel rolled -- And carried, I supposed -- to Heaven, For children, made of Gold --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut not to touch, or wish for, Or think of, with a sigh - And so and so -- had been to me, Had God willed differently.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI wish I knew that Woman's name -- So when she comes this way, To hold my life, and hold my ears For fear I hear her say\u13\'0d\u13\'0dShe's "sorry I am dead" -- again -- Just when the Grave and I -- Have sobbed ourselves almost to sleep, Our only Lullaby --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d589 The Night was wide, and furnished scant With but a single Star -- That often as a Cloud it met -- Blew out itself -- for fear --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Wind pursued the little Bush -And drove away the Leaves November left -- then clambered up And fretted in the Eaves --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNo Squirrel went abroad -- A Dog's belated feet Like intermittent Plush, he heard Adown the empty Street --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo feel if Blinds be fast - And closer to the fire - Her little Rocking Chair to draw -- And shiver for the Poor --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Housewife's gentle Task -- How pleasanter -- said she Unto the Sofa opposite - The Sleet -- than May, no Thee --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d590\u13\'0d\u13\'0dDid you ever stand in a Cavern's Mouth -- Widths out of the Sun -- And look -- and shudder, and block your breath -- And deem to be alone\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIn such a place, what horror, How Goblin it would be - And fly, as 'twere pursuing you? Then Loneliness -- looks so --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dDid you ever look in a Cannon's face -- Between whose Yellow eye -- And yours -- the Judgment intervened -- The Question of "To die" -- Extemporizing in your ear As cool as Satyr's Drums -- If you remember, and were saved -- It's liker so -- it seems --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d591\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo interrupt His Yellow Plan The Sun does not allow Caprices of the Atmosphere -- And even when the Snow\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHeaves Balls of Specks, like Vicious Boy Directly in His Eye -- Does not so much as turn His Head Busy with Majesty --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Tis His to stimulate the Earth -- And magnetize the Sea -- And bind Astronomy, in place, Yet Any passing by\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWould deem Ourselves -- the busier As the Minutest Bee That rides -- emits a Thunder -- A Bomb -- to justify --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d592\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhat care the Dead, for Chanticleer -- What care the Dead for Day? 'Tis late your Sunrise vex their face -- And Purple Ribaldry -- of Morning\u13\'0d\u13\'0dPour as blank on them As on the Tier of Wall The Mason builded, yesterday, And equally as cool --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhat care the Dead for Summer? The Solstice had no Sun Could waste the Snow before their Gate -- And knew One Bird a Tune -- Could thrill their Mortised Ear Of all the Birds that be - This One -- beloved of Mankind Henceforward cherished be --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhat care the Dead for Winter? Themselves as easy freeze -- June Noon -- as January Night -- As soon the South -- her Breeze\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOf Sycamore -- or Cinnamon -- Deposit in a Stone And put a Stone to keep it Warm -- Give Spices -- unto Men --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d593\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI think I was enchanted When first a sombre Girl -- I read that Foreign Lady -- The Dark -- felt beautiful --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd whether it was noon at night -Or only Heaven -- at Noon -- For very Lunacy of Light I had not power to tell --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Bees -- became as Butterflies - The Butterflies -- as Swans -- Approached -- and spurned the narrow Grass -- And just the meanest Tunes\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThat Nature murmured to herself To keep herself in Cheer -- I took for Giants -- practising Titanic Opera --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Days -- to Mighty Metres stept -- The Homeliest -- adorned As if unto a Jubilee 'Twere suddenly confirmed -- I could not have defined the change -Conversion of the Mind Like Sanctifying in the Soul -- Is witnessed -- not explained --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Twas a Divine Insanity -- The Danger to be Sane Should I again experience -- 'Tis Antidote to turn --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo Tomes of solid Witchcraft -- Magicians be asleep -- But Magic -- hath an Element Like Deity -- to keep --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d594\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Battle fought between the Soul And No Man -- is the One Of all the Battles prevalent -- By far the Greater One --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNo News of it is had abroad -- Its Bodiless Campaign Establishes, and terminates -- Invisible -- Unknown --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNor History -- record it - As Legions of a Night The Sunrise scatters -- These endure -- Enact -- and terminate --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d595\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLike Mighty Foot Lights -- burned the Red At Bases of the Trees - The far Theatricals of Day Exhibiting -- to These - 'Twas Universe -- that did applaud -While Chiefest -- of the Crowd -- Enabled by his Royal Dress -- Myself distinguished God --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d596\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhen I was small, a Woman died -- Today -- her Only Boy Went up from the Potomac -- His face all Victory\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo look at her -- How slowly The Seasons must have turned Till Bullets clipt an Angle And He passed quickly round --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIf pride shall be in Paradise -- Ourself cannot decide -Of their imperial Conduct -- No person testified --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut, proud in Apparition -- That Woman and her Boy Pass back and forth, before my Brain As even in the sky --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI'm confident that Bravoes -- Perpetual break abroad For Braveries, remote as this In Scarlet Maryland --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d597\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt always felt to me -- a wrong To that Old Moses -- done -- To let him see -- the Canaan -- Without the entering --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd tho' in soberer moments -- No Moses there can be I'm satisfied -- the Romance In point of injury --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSurpasses sharper stated -- Of Stephen -- or of Paul -- For these -- were only put to death -While God's adroiter will\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOn Moses -- seemed to fasten With tantalizing Play As Boy -- should deal with lesser Boy -- To prove ability.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe fault -- was doubtless Israel's -Myself -- had banned the Tribes -- And ushered Grand Old Moses In Pentateuchal Robes\u13\'0d\u13\'0dUpon the Broad Possession 'Twas little -- But titled Him -- to see -- Old Man on Nebo! Late as this -- My justice bleeds -- for Thee!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d598\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThree times -- we parted -- Breath -- and I -- Three times -- He would not go -- But strove to stir the lifeless Fan The Waters -- strove to stay.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThree Times -- the Billows tossed me up -- Then caught me -- like a Ball -- Then made Blue faces in my face -- And pushed away a sail\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThat crawled Leagues off -- I liked to see -- For thinking -- while I die -- How pleasant to behold a Thing Where Human faces -- be --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Waves grew sleepy -- Breath -- did not -- The Winds -- like Children -- lulled -Then Sunrise kissed my Chrysalis -- And I stood up -- and lived --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d599\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThere is a pain -- so utter -- It swallows substance up -- Then covers the Abyss with Trance -- So Memory can step Around -- across -- upon it -- As one within a Swoon -- Goes safely -- where an open eye -- Would drop Him -- Bone by Bone.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dPoems No. 600-699\u13\'0d\u13\'0d600\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt troubled me as once I was -- For I was once a Child - Concluding how an Atom -- fell -- And yet the Heavens -- held --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Heavens weighed the most -- by far -- Yet Blue -- and solid -- stood -- Without a Bolt -- that I could prove -- Would Giants -- understand?\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLife set me larger -- problems -- Some I shall keep -- to solve Till Algebra is easier -- Or simpler proved -- above --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThen -- too -- be comprehended -- What sorer -- puzzled me -- Why Heaven did not break away -- And tumble -- Blue -- on me --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d601\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA still -- Volcano -- Life - That flickered in the night -- When it was dark enough to do Without erasing sight --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA quiet -- Earthquake Style -- Too subtle to suspect By natures this side Naples -- The North cannot detect\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Solemn -- Torrid -- Symbol -- The lips that never lie -- Whose hissing Corals part -- and shut -- And Cities -- ooze away -- 602\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOf Brussels -- it was not -- Of Kidderminster? Nay -- The Winds did buy it of the Woods -They -- sold it unto me\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt was a gentle price -- The poorest -- could afford -- It was within the frugal purse Of Beggar -- or of Bird --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOf small and spicy Yards -- In hue -- a mellow Dun -- Of Sunshine -- and of Sere -- Composed}
