ion compassed And never winced before.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI fitted to the Latch My Hand, with trembling care Lest back the awful Door should spring And leave me in the Floor --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThen moved my Fingers off As cautiously as Glass And held my ears, and like a Thief Fled gasping from the House --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d610\u13\'0d\u13\'0dYou'll find -- it when you try to die -- The Easier to let go -- For recollecting such as went -- You could not spare -- you know.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd though their places somewhat filled -- As did their Marble names With Moss -- they never grew so full -- You chose the newer names --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd when this World -- sets further back -- As Dying -- say it does -- The former love -- distincter grows -- And supersedes the fresh --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd Thought of them -- so fair invites -- It looks too tawdry Grace To stay behind -- with just the Toys We bought -- to ease their place --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d611\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI see thee better -- in the Dark -- I do not need a Light - The Love of Thee -- a Prism be -- Excelling Violet --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI see thee better for the Years That hunch themselves between -- The Miner's Lamp -- sufficient be -- To nullify the Mine --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd in the Grave -- I see Thee best -Its little Panels be Aglow -- All ruddy -- with the Light I held so high, for Thee --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhat need of Day -- To Those whose Dark -- hath so -- surpassing Sun -- It deem it be -- Continually -- At the Meridian?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d612\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt would have starved a Gnat -- To live so small as I -- And yet I was a living Child -- With Food's necessity\u13\'0d\u13\'0dUpon me -- like a Claw -- I could no more remove Than I could coax a Leech away -- Or make a Dragon -- move --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNot like the Gnat -- had I -- The privilege to fly And seek a Dinner for myself -- How mightier He -- than I --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNor like Himself -- the Art Upon the Window Pane To gad my little Being out -- And not begin --