\u13\'0dAnd next -- I met her on a Cloud -- Myself too far below To follow her superior Road -- Or its advantage -- Blue --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d630\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Lightning playeth -- all the while -- But when He singeth -- then -- Ourselves are conscious He exist -- And we approach Him -- stern --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWith Insulators -- and a Glove -- Whose short -- sepulchral Bass Alarms us -- tho' His Yellow feet May pass -- and counterpass --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dUpon the Ropes -- above our Head -- Continual -- with the News -- Nor We so much as check our speech -- Nor stop to cross Ourselves --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d631\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOurselves were wed one summer -- dear -- Your Vision -- was in June -- And when Your little Lifetime failed, I wearied -- too -- of mine --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd overtaken in the Dark -- Where You had put me down -- By Some one carrying a Light -- I -- too -- received the Sign.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Tis true -- Our Futures different lay -- Your Cottage -- faced the sun -- While Oceans -- and the North must be -- On every side of mine\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Tis true, Your Garden led the Bloom, For mine -- in Frosts -- was sown -- And yet, one Summer, we were Queens -- But You -- were crowned in June --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d632\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Brain -- is wider than the Sky -- For -- put them side by side -- The one the other will contain With ease -- and You -- beside --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Brain is deeper than the sea -For -- hold them -- Blue to Blue -- The one the other will absorb -- As Sponges -- Buckets -- do --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Brain is just the weight of God -- For -- Heft them -- Pound for Pound -- And they will differ -- if they do -- As Syllable from Sound --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d633\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhen Bells stop ringing -- Church -- begins The Positive -- of Bells - When Cogs -- stop -- that's Circumference -- The Ultimate -- of Wheels.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMy Portion is Defeat -- today -- A paler luck than Victory -- Less Paeans -- fewer Bells -- The Drums don't foll