ld not drink it, Sweet, Till You had tasted first, Though cooler than the Water was The Thoughtfullness of Thirst.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d819\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAll I may, if small, Do it not display Larger for the Totalness -- 'Tis Economy\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo bestow a World And withhold a Star -- Utmost, is Munificence -- Less, tho' larger, poor.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d820\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAll Circumstances are the Frame In which His Face is set -- All Latitudes exist for His Sufficient Continent --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Light His Action, and the Dark The Leisure of His Will - In Him Existence serve or set A Force illegible.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d821\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAway from Home are some and I -- An Emigrant to be In a Metropolis of Homes Is easy, possibly -- The Habit of a Foreign Sky We -- difficult -- acquire As Children, who remain in Face The more their Feet retire.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d822\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThis Consciousness that is aware Of Neighbors and the Sun Will be the one aware of Death And that itself alone\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIs traversing the interval Experience between And most profound experiment Appointed unto Men --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHow adequate unto itself Its properties shall be Itself unto itself and none Shall make discovery.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAdventure most unto itself The Soul condemned to be -- Attended by a single Hound Its own identity.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d823\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNot that We did, shall be the test When Act and Will are done But what Our Lord infers We would Had We diviner been --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d824 [first version]\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Wind begun to knead the Grass -- As Women do a Dough -- He flung a Hand full at the Plain -- A Hand full at the Sky -- The Leaves unhooked themselves from Trees -- And started all abroad - The Dust did scoop itself like Hands -- And throw away the Road -- The Wagons -- quickened on the Street -- The Thunders gossiped low -- The Lightning showed a Yellow Head -- And then a livid Toe -- The Birds put up the Bars to Nests - The Cattle flung to Barns -- Then came one drop of Giant Rain -- And then, as if the Hands That held the Dams -- had parted hold -- The Waters Wrecked the Sky -- But overlooked my Father's House -- Just Quartering a Tree -\u13\'0d\u13\'0d[second version]\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Wind begun to rock the Grass With threatening Tunes and low -- He threw a Menace at the Earth -- A Menace at the Sky.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Leaves unhooked themselves from Trees -- And started all abroad The Dust did scoop itself like Hands And threw away the Road.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Wagons quickened on the Streets The Thunder hurried slow -- The Lightning showed a Yellow Beak And then a livid Claw.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Birds put up the Bars to Nests -The Cattle fled to Barns -- There came one drop of Giant Rain And then as if the Hands\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThat held the Dams had parted hold The Waters Wrecked the Sky, But overlooked my Father's House -- Just quartering a Tree --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d825\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAn Hour is a Sea Between a few, and me -- With them would Harbor be --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d826\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLove reckons by itself -- alone -- "As large as I" -- relate the Sun To One who never felt it blaze -- Itself is all the like it has --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d827\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Only News I know Is Bulletins all Day From Immortality.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Only Shows I see -Tomorrow and Today -- Perchance Eternity --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Only One I meet Is God -- The Only Street -- Existence -- This traversed\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIf Other News there be -- Or Admirable Show -- I'll tell it You -- The Robin is the One That interrupt the Morn With hurried -- few -- express Reports When March is scarcely on --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Robin is the One That overflow the Noon With her cherubic quantity -- An April but begun --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Robin is the One That speechless from her Nest Submit that Home -- and Certainty And Sanctity, are best\u13\'0d\u13\'0d829\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAmple make this Bed -Make this Bed with Awe -- In it wait till Judgment break Excellent and Fair.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBe its Mattress straight -- Be its Pillow round -- Let no Sunrise' yellow noise Interrupt this Ground --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d830\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo this World she returned. But with a tinge of that -A Compound manner, As a Sod Espoused a Violet, That chiefer to the Skies Than to himself, allied, Dwelt hesitating, half of Dust, And half of Day, the Bride. 831\u13\'0d\u13\'0dDying! To be afraid of thee One must to thine Artillery Have left exposed a Friend -- Than thine old Arrow is a Shot Delivered straighter to the Heart The leaving Love behind.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNot for itself, the Dust is shy, But, enemy, Beloved be Thy Batteries divorce. Fight sternly in a Dying eye Two Armies, Love and Certainty And Love and the Reverse.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d832\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSoto! Explore thyself! Therein thyself shalt find The "Undiscovered Continent" -- No Settler had the Mind.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d833\u13\'0d\u13\'0dPerhaps you think me stooping I'm not ashamed of that Christ -- stooped until He touched the Grave -- Do those at Sacrament\u13\'0d\u13\'0dCommemorative Dishonor Or love annealed of love Until it bend as low as Death Redignified, above? Before He comes we weigh the Time! 'Tis Heavy and 'tis Light. When He depart, an Emptiness Is the prevailing Freight.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d835\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNature and God -- I neither knew Yet Both so well knew me They startled, like Executors Of My identity.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dYet Neither told -- that I could learn -My Secret as secure As Herschel's private interest Or Mercury's affair --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d836\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTruth -- is as old as God -- His Twin identity And will endure as long as He A Co-Eternity --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd perish on the Day Himself is borne away From Mansion of the Universe A lifeless Deity.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d837\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHow well I knew Her not Whom not to know has been A Bounty in prospective, now Next Door to mine the Pain. Impossibility, like Wine Exhilarates the Man Who tastes it; Possibility Is flavorless -- Combine\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Chance's faintest Tincture And in the former Dram Enchantment makes ingredient As certainly as Doom --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d839\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAlways Mine! No more Vacation! Term of Light this Day begun! Failless as the fair rotation Of the Seasons and the Sun.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOld the Grace, but new the Subjects -- Old, indeed, the East, Yet upon His Purple Programme Every Dawn, is first.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d840\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI cannot buy it -- 'tis not sold -- There is no other in the World -- Mine was the only one\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI was so happy I forgot To shut the Door And it went out And I am all alone --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIf I could find it Anywhere I would not mind the journey there Though it took all my store\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut just to look it in the Eye -- "Did'st thou?" "Thou did'st not mean," to say, Then, turn my Face away. 841\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Moth the hue of this Haunts Candles in Brazil. Nature's Experience would make Our Reddest Second pale.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNature is fond, I sometimes think, Of Trinkets, as a Girl. 842\u13\'0d\u13\'0dGood to hide, and hear 'em hunt! Better, to be found, If one care to, that is, The Fox fits the Hound --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dGood to know, and not tell, Best, to know and tell, Can one find the rare Ear Not too dull --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d843\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI made slow Riches but my Gain Was steady as the Sun And every Night, it numbered more Than the preceding One\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAll Days, I did not earn the same But my perceiveless Gain Inferred the less by Growing than The Sum that it had grown. Spring is the Period Express from God. Among the other seasons Himself abide,\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut during March and April None stir abroad Without a cordial interview With God.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d845\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBe Mine the Doom -- Sufficient Fame -- To perish in Her Hand!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d846\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTwice had Summer her fair Verdure Proffered to the Plain - Twice a Winter's silver Fracture On the Rivers been --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTwo full Autumns for the Squirrel Bounteous prepared -- Nature, Had'st thou not a Berry For thy wandering Bird?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d847\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFinite -- to fail, but infinite to Venture -- For the one ship that struts the shore Many's the gallant -- overwhelmed Creature Nodding in Navies nevermore -- Just as He spoke it from his Hands This Edifice remain -- A Turret more, a Turret less Dishonor his Design --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAccording as his skill prefer It perish, or endure -- Content, soe'er, it ornament His absent character.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d849\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe good Will of a Flower The Man who would possess Must first present Certificate Of minted Holiness.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d850\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI sing to use the Waiting My Bonnet but to tie And shut the Door unto my House No more to do have I\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTill His best step approaching We journey to the Day And tell each other how We sung To Keep the Dark away.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d851\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhen the Astronomer stops seeking For his Pleiad's Face -- When the lone British Lady Forsakes the Arctic Race\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhen to his Covenant Needle The Sailor doubting turns -- It will be amply early To ask what treason means.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d852\u13\'0d\u13\'0dApology for Her Be rendered by the Bee -- Herself, without a Parliament Apology for Me.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d853\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhen One has given up One's life The parting with the rest Feels}
