easy, as when Day lets go Entirely the West\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Peaks, that lingered last Remain in Her regret As scarcely as the Iodine Upon the Cataract.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d854\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBanish Air from Air -- Divide Light if you dare -- They'll meet While Cubes in a Drop Or Pellets of Shape Fit Films cannot annul Odors return whole Force Flame And with a Blonde push Over your impotence Flits Steam. 855\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo own the Art within the Soul The Soul to entertain With Silence as a Company And Festival maintain\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIs an unfurnished Circumstance Possession is to One As an Estate perpetual Or a reduceless Mine.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d856\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThere is a finished feeling Experienced at Graves -- A leisure of the Future -- A Wilderness of Size.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBy Death's bold Exhibition Preciser what we are And the Eternal function Enabled to infer.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d857\u13\'0d\u13\'0dUncertain lease -- develops lustre On Time Uncertain Grasp, appreciation Of Sum --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe shorter Fate -- is oftener the chiefest Because Inheritors upon a tenure Prize -- This Chasm, Sweet, upon my life I mention it to you, When Sunrise through a fissure drop The Day must follow too.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIf we demur, its gaping sides Disclose as 'twere a Tomb Ourself am lying straight wherein The Favorite of Doom.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhen it has just contained a Life Then, Darling, it will close And yet so bolder every Day So turbulent it grows\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI'm tempted half to stitch it up With a remaining Breath I should not miss in yielding, though To Him, it would be Death --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd so I bear it big about My Burial -- before A Life quite ready to depart Can harass me no more --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d859\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA doubt if it be Us Assists the staggering Mind In an extremer Anguish Until it footing find.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAn Unreality is lent, A merciful Mirage That makes the living possible While it suspends the lives. Absence disembodies -- so does Death Hiding individuals from the Earth Superposition helps, as well as love -- Tenderness decreases as we prove --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d861\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSplit the Lark -- and you'll find the Music -- Bulb after Bulb, in Silver rolled -- Scantilly dealt to the Summer Morning Saved for your Ear when Lutes be old.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLoose the Flood -- you shall find it patent -- Gush after Gush, reserved for you -- Scarlet Experiment! Sceptic Thomas! Now, do you doubt that your Bird was true?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d862\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLight is sufficient to itself -- If Others want to see It can be had on Window Panes Some Hours in the Day.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut not for Compensation -- It holds as large a Glow To Squirrel in the Himmaleh Precisely, as to you.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d863\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThat Distance was between Us That is not of Mile or Main -- The Will it is that situates -- Equator -- never can -- The Robin for the Crumb Returns no syllable But long records the Lady's name In Silver Chronicle.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d865\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHe outstripped Time with but a Bout, He outstripped Stars and Sun And then, unjaded, challenged God In presence of the Throne.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd He and He in mighty List Unto this present, run, The larger Glory for the less A just sufficient Ring.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d866\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFame is the tine that Scholars leave Upon their Setting Names -- The Iris not of Occident That disappears as comes --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d867\u13\'0d\u13\'0dEscaping backward to perceive The Sea upon our place -- Escaping forward, to confront His glittering Embrace --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dRetreating up, a Billow's height Retreating blinded down Our undermining feet to meet Instructs to the Divine. They ask but our Delight -- The Darlings of the Soil And grant us all their Countenance For a penurious smile.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d869\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBecause the Bee may blameless hum For Thee a Bee do I become List even unto Me.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBecause the Flowers unafraid May lift a look on thine, a Maid Alway a Flower would be.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNor Robins, Robins need not hide When Thou upon their Crypts intrude So Wings bestow on Me Or Petals, or a Dower of Buzz That Bee to ride, or Flower of Furze I that way worship Thee.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d870\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFinding is the first Act The second, loss, Third, Expedition for The "Golden Fleece"\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFourth, no Discovery -- Fifth, no Crew -- Finally, no Golden Fleece -- Jason -- sham -- too. The Sun and Moon must make their haste -- The Stars express around For in the Zones of Paradise The Lord alone is burned --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHis Eye, it is the East and West -- The North and South when He Do concentrate His Countenance Like Glow Worms, flee away --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOh Poor and Far -- Oh Hindred Eye That hunted for the Day -- The Lord a Candle entertains Entirely for Thee --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d872\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAs the Starved Maelstrom laps the Navies As the Vulture teased Forces the Broods in lonely Valleys As the Tiger eased\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBy but a Crumb of Blood, fasts Scarlet Till he meet a Man Dainty adorned with Veins and Tissues And partakes -- his Tongue\u13\'0d\u13\'0dCooled by the Morsel for a moment Grows a fiercer thing Till he esteem his Dates and Cocoa A Nutrition mean\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI, of a finer Famine Deem my Supper dry For but a Berry of Domingo And a Torrid Eye. Ribbons of the Year -- Multitude Brocade -- Worn to Nature's Party once\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThen, as flung aside As a faded Bead Or a Wrinkled Pearl Who shall charge the Vanity Of the Maker's Girl?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d874\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThey won't frown always -- some sweet Day When I forget to tease - They'll recollect how cold I looked And how I just said "Please."\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThen They will hasten to the Door To call the little Girl Who cannot thank Them for the Ice That filled the lisping full.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d875\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI stepped from Plank to Plank A slow and cautious way The Stars about my Head I felt About my Feet the Sea.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI knew not but the next Would be my final inch - This gave me that precarious Gait Some call Experience.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d876\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt was a Grave, yet bore no Stone Enclosed 'twas not of Rail A Consciousness its Acre, and It held a Human Soul.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dEntombed by whom, for what offence If Home or Foreign born -- Had I the curiosity 'Twere not appeased of men\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTill Resurrection, I must guess Denied the small desire A Rose upon its Ridge to sow Or take away a Briar.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d877\u13\'0d\u13\'0dEach Scar I'll keep for Him Instead I'll say of Gem In His long Absence worn A Costlier one\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut every Tear I bore Were He to count them o'er His own would fall so more I'll mis sum them.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d878\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Sun is gay or stark According to our Deed. If Merry, He is merrier -- If eager for the Dead\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOr an expended Day He helped to make too bright His mighty pleasure suits Us not It magnifies our Freight Each Second is the last Perhaps, recalls the Man Just measuring unconsciousness The Sea and Spar between.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo fail within a Chance -- How terribler a thing Than perish from the Chance's list Before the Perishing!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d880\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Bird must sing to earn the Crumb What merit have the Tune No Breakfast if it guaranty\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Rose content may bloom To gain renown of Lady's Drawer But if the Lady come But once a Century, the Rose Superfluous become --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d881\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI've none to tell me to but Thee So when Thou failest, nobody. It was a little tie -- It just held Two, nor those it held Since Somewhere thy sweet Face has spilled Beyond my Boundary --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIf things were opposite -- and Me And Me it were -- that ebbed from Thee On some unanswering Shore -- Would'st Thou seek so -- just say That I the Answer may pursue Unto the lips it eddied through -- So -- overtaking Thee - A Shade upon the mind there passes As when on Noon A Cloud the mighty Sun encloses Remembering\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThat some there be too numb to notice Oh God Why give if Thou must take away The Loved?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d883\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Poets light but Lamps -- Themselves -- go out -- The Wicks they stimulate -- If vital Light\u13\'0d\u13\'0dInhere as do the Suns -- Each Age a Lens Disseminating their Circumference --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d884\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAs Everywhere of Silver With Ropes of Sand To keep it from effacing The Track called Land.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d885\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOur little Kinsmen -- after Rain In plenty may be seen, A Pink and Pulpy multitude The tepid Ground upon.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA needless life, it seemed to me Until a little Bird As to a Hospitality Advanced and breakfasted.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAs I of He, so God of Me I pondered, may have judged, And left the little Angle Worm With Modesties enlarged.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d886\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThese tested Our Horizon -- Then disappeared As Birds before achieving A Latitude.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOur Retrospection of Them A fixed Delight, But our Anticipation A Dice -- a Doubt --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d887\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWe outgrow love, like other things And put it in the Drawer -- Till it an Antique fashion shows -- Like Costumes Grandsires wore.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d888\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhen I have seen the Sun emerge From His amazing House -- And leave a Day at every Door A Deed, in every place --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWithout the incident of Fame Or accident of Noise -- The Earth has seemed to me a Drum, Pursued of little Boys Crisis is a Hair Toward which the forces creep Past which forces retrograde If it come in sleep\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo suspend the Breath Is the most we can Ignorant is it Life or Death Nicely balancing.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLet an instant push Or an Atom press Or a Circle hesitate In Circumference\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt -- may jolt the Hand That adjusts the Hair That secures Eternity From presenting -- Here --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d890\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFrom Us She wandered now a Year, Her tarrying, unknown, If Wilderness prevent her feet Or that Ethereal Zone\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNo eye hath seen and lived We ignorant must be -- We only know what time of Year We took the Mystery.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d891\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo my quick ear the Leaves -- conferred -- The Bushes -- they were Bells -- I could not find a Privacy From Nature's sentinels --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIn Cave if I presumed to hide The Walls -- begun to tell -- Creation seemed a mighty Crack -- To make me visible --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d892\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWho occupies this House? A Stranger I must judge Since No one know His Circumstance -- 'Tis well the name and age\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAre writ upon the Door Or I should fear to pause Where not so much as Honest Dog Approach encourages.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt seems a curious Town -- Some Houses very old, Some -- newly raised this Afternoon, Were I compelled to build\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt should not be among Inhabitants so still But where the Birds assemble And Boys were possible.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBefore Myself was born 'Twas settled, so they say, A Territory for the Ghosts -- And Squirrels, formerly.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dUntil a Pioneer, as Settlers often do Liking the quiet of the Place Attracted more unto --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd from a Settlement A Capital has grown Distinguished for the gravity Of every Citizen.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Owner of this House A Stranger He must be -- Eternity's Acquaintances Are}
