e to Them now, Homesickness After Eternity.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNot if the Just suspect me And offer a Reward Would I restore my Booty To that Bold Person, God --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d901\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSweet, to have had them lost For news that they be saved -- The nearer they departed Us The nearer they, restored,\u13\'0d\u13\'0dShall stand to Our Right Hand -- Most precious and the Dead -- Next precious Those that rose to go - Then thought of Us, and stayed. The first Day that I was a Life I recollect it -- How still -That last Day that I was a Life I recollect it -- as well -\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Twas stiller -- though the first Was still -- "Twas empty -- but the first Was full --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThis -- was my finallest Occasion -But then My tenderer Experiment Toward Men --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d"Which choose I"? That -- I cannot say -- "Which choose They"? Question Memory!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d903\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI hide myself within my flower, That fading from your Vase, You, unsuspecting, feel for me -- Almost a loneliness.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d904\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHad I not This, or This, I said, Appealing to Myself, In moment of prosperity -- Inadequate -- were Life --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d"Thou hast not Me, nor Me" -- it said, In Moment of Reverse -- "And yet Thou art industrious -- No need -- hadst Thou -- of us"?\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMy need -- was all I had -- I said -- The need did not reduce -- Because the food -- exterminate -- The hunger -- does not cease --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut diligence -- is sharper -- Proportioned to the Chance -- To feed upon the Retrograde -- Enfeebles -- the Advance --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d905\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBetween My Country -- and the Others -- There is a Sea -- But Flowers -- negotiate between us -- As Ministry.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d906\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Admirations -- and Contempts -- of time -- Show justest -- through an Open Tomb -- The Dying -- as it were a Height Reorganizes Estimate And what We saw not We distinguish clear -- And mostly -- see not What We saw before --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Tis Compound Vision - Light -- enabling Light - The Finite -- furnished With the Infinite -- Convex -- and Concave Witness -Back -- toward Time -- And forward -- Toward the God of Him -- Till Death -- is narrow Loving -- The scantest Heart extant Will hold you till your privilege Of Finiteness -- be spent --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut He whose loss procures you Such Destitution that Your Life too abject for itself Thenceforward imitate --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dUntil -- Resemblance perfect -- Yourself, for His pursuit Delight of Nature -- abdicate -- Exhibit Love -- somewhat --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d908\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Tis Sunrise -- Little Maid -- Hast Thou No Station in the Day? 'Twas not thy wont, to hinder so -- Retrieve thine industry --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Tis Noon -- My little Maid -- Alas -- and art thou sleeping yet? The Lily -- waiting to be Wed -- The Bee -- Hast thou forgot?\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMy little Maid -- 'Tis Night -- Alas That Night should be to thee Instead of Morning -- Had'st thou broached Thy little Plan to Die -- Dissuade thee, if I could not, Sweet, I might have aided -- thee --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d909\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI make His Crescent fill or lack -- His Nature is at Full Or Quarter -- as I signify -- His Tides -- do I control - He holds superior in the Sky Or gropes, at my Command Behind inferior Clouds -- or round A Mist's slow Colonnade --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut since We hold a Mutual Disc -- And front a Mutual Day -- Which is the Despot, neither knows -Nor Whose -- the Tyranny --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d910\u13\'0d\u13\'0dExperience is the Angled Road Preferred against the Mind By -- Paradox -- the Mind itself -- Presuming it to lead\u13\'0d\u13\'0dQuite Opposite -- How Complicate The Discipline of Man -- Compelling Him to Choose Himself His Preappointed Pain -\u13\'0d\u13\'0d911\u13\'0d\u13\'0dToo little way the House must lie From every Human Heart That holds in undisputed Lease A white inhabitant --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dToo narrow is the Right between -- Too imminent the chan