ife the Aching Or cool one Pain\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOr help one fainting Robin Unto his Nest again I shall not live in Vain.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d920\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWe can but follow to the Sun -- As oft as He go down He leave Ourselves a Sphere behind -- 'Tis mostly -- following -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWe go no further with the Dust Than to the Earthen Door -- And then the Panels are reversed -- And we behold -- no more.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d921\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIf it had no pencil Would it try mine -- Worn -- now -- and dull -- sweet, Writing much to thee. If it had no word, Would it make the Daisy, Most as big as I was, When it plucked me? 922\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThose who have been in the Grave the longest -Those who begin Today -- Equally perish from our Practise -- Death is the other way --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFoot of the Bold did least attempt it -- It -- is the White Exploit -- Once to achieve, annuls the power Once to communicate --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d923\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHow the Waters closed above Him We shall never know -- How He stretched His Anguish to us That -- is covered too --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSpreads the Pond Her Base of Lilies Bold above the Boy Whose unclaimed Hat and Jacket Sum the History --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d924\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLove -- is that later Thing than Death -- More previous -- than Life -- Confirms it at its entrance -- And Usurps it -- of itself --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTastes Death -- the first -- to hand the sting The Second -- to its friend -- Disarms the little interval -- Deposits Him with God --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThen hovers -- an inferior Guard -- Lest this Beloved Charge Need -- once in an Eternity -- A smaller than the Large --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d925\u13\'0d\u13\'0dStruck, was I, not yet by Lightning -Lightning -- lets away Power to perceive His Process With Vitality.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMaimed -- was I -- yet not by Venture -- Stone of stolid Boy -- Nor a Sportsman's Peradventure -- Who mine Enemy?\u13\'0d\u13\'0dRobbed -- was I -- intact to Bandit -- All my Mansion torn -- Sun -- withdra