Places, we Like Individuals go Who something lost, the seeking for Is all that's left them, now --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d936\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThis Dust, and its Feature -- Accredited -- Today -- Will in a second Future -- Cease to identify --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThis Mind, and its measure -- A too minute Area For its enlarged inspection's Comparison -- appear --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThis World, and its species A too concluded show For its absorbed Attention's Remotest scrutiny --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d937\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI felt a Cleaving in my Mind -- As if my Brain had split -- I tried to match it -- Seam by Seam -- But could not make it fit. The thought behind, I strove to join Unto the thought before -- But Sequence ravelled out of Sound Like Balls -- upon a Floor.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d938\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFairer through Fading -- as the Day Into the Darkness dips away -- Half Her Complexion of the Sun -- Hindering -- Haunting -- Perishing -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dRallies Her Glow, like a dying Friend -- Teasing with glittering Amend -- Only to aggravate the Dark Through an expiring -- perfect -- look --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d939\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhat I see not, I better see -- Through Faith -- my Hazel Eye Has periods of shutting -But, No lid has Memory --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFor frequent, all my sense obscured I equally behold As someone held a light unto The Features so beloved ---\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd I arise -- and in my Dream -- Do Thee distinguished Grace -- Till jealous Daylight interrupt -- And mar thy perfectness --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d940\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOn that dear Frame the Years had worn Yet precious as the House In which We first experienced Light The Witnessing, to Us - Precious! It was conceiveless fair As Hands the Grave had grimed Should softly place within our own Denying that they died.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d941\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Lady feeds Her little Bird At rarer intervals -- The little Bird would not dissent But meekly recognize\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Gulf between the Hand and Her And crumbless and afar And fain