Swift as a Freshet's Tongue So of the Flower of the Soul Its process is unknown.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhen it is found, a few rejoice The Wise convey it Home Carefully cherishing the spot If other Flower become.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhen it is lost, that Day shall be The Funeral of God, Upon his Breast, a closing Soul The Flower of our Lord.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d946\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt is an honorable Thought And make One lift One's Hat As One met sudden Gentlefolk Upon a daily Street\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThat We've immortal Place Though Pyramids decay And Kingdoms, like the Orchard Flit Russetly away\u13\'0d\u13\'0d947\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOf Tolling Bell I ask the cause? "A Soul has gone to Heaven" I'm answered in a lonesome tone -- Is Heaven then a Prison?\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThat Bells should ring till all should know A Soul had gone to Heaven Would seem to me the more the way A Good News should be given.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d948\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Twas Crisis -- All the length had passed -- That dull -- benumbing time There is in Fever or Event -- And now the Chance had come --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe instant holding in its claw The privilege to live Or warrant to report the Soul The other side the Grave.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Muscles grappled as with leads That would not let the Will -- The Spirit shook the Adamant -- But could not make it feel.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Second poised -- debated -- shot -- Another had begun -- And simultaneously, a Soul Escaped the House unseen --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d949\u13\'0d\u13\'0dUnder the Light, yet under, Under the Grass and the Dirt, Under the Beetle's Cellar Under the Clover's Root,\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFurther than Arm could stretch Were it Giant long, Further than Sunshine could Were the Day Year long,\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOver the Light, yet over, Over the Arc of the Bird -- Over the Comet's chimney -- Over the Cubit's Head,\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFurther than Guess can gallop Further than Riddle ride -- Oh for a Disc to the Distance Between Ourselves and the Dead!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d950\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Sunset stopped on Cottages Where Sunset hence must be For treason not of His, but Life's, Gone Westerly, Today --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Sunset stopped on Cottages Where Morning just begun -- What difference, after all, Thou mak'st Thou supercilious Sun?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d951\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAs Frost is best conceived By force of its Result -- Affliction is inferred By subsequent effect -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIf when the sun reveal, The Garden keep the Gash -- If as the Days resume The wilted countenance\u13\'0d\u13\'0dCannot correct the crease Or counteract the stain -- Presumption is Vitality Was somewhere put in twain.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d952\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Man may make a Remark -- In itself -- a quiet thing That may furnish the Fuse unto a Spark In dormant nature -- lain --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLet us deport -- with skill -- Let us discourse -- with care -- Powder exists in Charcoal -- Before it exists in Fire.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d953\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Door just opened on a street -- I -- lost -- was passing by -- An instant's Width of Warmth disclosed -- And Wealth -- and Company.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Door as instant shut -- And I -- I -- lost -- was passing by -- Lost doubly -- but by contrast -- most -- Informing -- misery --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d954\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Chemical conviction That Nought be lost Enable in Disaster My fractured Trust -- The Faces of the Atoms If I shall see How more the Finished Creatures Departed me!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d955\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Hollows round His eager Eyes Were Pages where to read Pathetic Histories -- although Himself had not complained. Biography to All who passed Of Unobtrusive Pain Except for the italic Face Endured, unhelped -- unknown.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d956\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhat shall I do when the Summer troubles -- What, when the Rose is ripe -- What when the Eggs fly off in Music From the Maple Keep?\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhat shall I do when the Skies a'chirrup Drop a Tune on me -- When the Bee hangs all Noon in the Buttercup What will become of me?\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOh, when the Squirrel fills His Pockets And the Berries stare How can I bear their jocund Faces Thou from Here, so far?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Twouldn't afflict a Robin -- All His Goods have Wings -- I -- do not fly, so wherefore My Perennial Things? 957\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAs One does Sickness over In convalescent Mind, His scrutiny of Chances By blessed Health obscured --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAs One rewalks a Precipice And whittles at the Twig That held Him from Perdition Sown sidewise in the Crag\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Custom of the Soul Far after suffering Identity to question For evidence't has been --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d958\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWe met as Sparks -- Diverging Flints Sent various -- scattered ways -- We parted as the Central Flint Were cloven with an Adze -- Subsisting on the Light We bore Before We felt the Dark -- A Flint unto this Day -- perhaps -- But for that single Spark.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d959\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA loss of something ever felt I -- The first that I could recollect Bereft I was -- of what I knew not Too young that any should suspect\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Mourner walked among the children I notwithstanding went about As one bemoaning a Dominion Itself the only Prince cast out -- Elder, Today, a session wiser And fainter, too, as Wiseness is -- I find myself still softly searching For my Delinguent Palaces --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd a Suspicion, like}
