ll sigh -- "The Other -- She -- is Where?" The Love, tho', will array me right I shall be perfect -- in His sight --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIf He perceive the other Truth -- Upon an Excellenter Youth --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHow sweet I shall not lack in Vain - But gain -- thro' loss -- Through Grief -- obtain -The Beauty that reward Him best -- The Beauty of Demand -- at Rest --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d969\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHe who in Himself believes -- Fraud cannot presume -- Faith is Constancy's Result -- And assumes -- from Home --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dCannot perish, though it fail Every second time -- But defaced Vicariously -- For Some Other Shame --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d970\u13\'0d\u13\'0dColor -- Caste -- Denomination -- These -- are Time's Affair -- Death's diviner Classifying Does not know they are --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAs in sleep -- All Hue forgotten -- Tenets -- put behind -- Death's large -- Democratic fingers Rub away the Brand -- If Circassian -- He is careless -- If He put away Chrysalis of Blonde -- or Umber -- Equal Butterfly --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThey emerge from His Obscuring -- What Death -- knows so well -- Our minuter intuitions -- Deem unplausible --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d971\u13\'0d\u13\'0dRobbed by Death -- but that was easy -- To the failing Eye I could hold the latest Glowing -- Robbed by Liberty\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFor Her Jugular Defences -- This, too, I endured -- Hint of Glory -- it afforded -- For the Brave Beloved --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFraud of Distance -- Fraud of Danger, Fraud of Death -- to bear -- It is Bounty -- to Suspense's Vague Calamity --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dStalking our entire Possession On a Hair's result -- Then -- seesawing -- coolly -- on it -- Trying if it split --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d972\u13\'0d\u13\'0dUnfulfilled to Observation -- Incomplete -- to Eye -- But to Faith -- a Revolution In Locality -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dUnto Us -- the Suns extinguish -- To our Opposite -- New Horizons -- they embellish -- Fronting Us -- with Night. 973\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Twas awkward, but it fitted me -- An Ancient fashioned Heart -- Its only lore -- its Steadfastness -- In Change -- unerudite -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt only moved as do the Suns -- For merit of Return -- Or Birds -- confirmed perpetual By Alternating Zone --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI only have it not Tonight In its established place -For technicality of Death -- Omitted in the Lease -\u13\'0d\u13\'0d974\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Soul's distinct connection With immortality Is best disclosed by Danger Or quick Calamity --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAs Lightning on a Landscape Exhibits Sheets of Place -- Not yet suspected -- but for Flash -And Click -- and Suddenness.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d975\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Mountain sat upon the Plain In his tremendous Chair -- His observation omnifold, His inquest, everywhere --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Seasons played around his knees Like Children round a sire -- Grandfather of the Days is He Of Dawn, the Ancestor -\u13\'0d\u13\'0d976\u13\'0d\u13\'0dDeath is a Dialogue between The Spirit and the Dust. "Dissolve" says Death -- The Spirit "Sir I have another Trust" --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dDeath doubts it -- Argues from the Ground -- The Spirit turns away Just laying off for evidence An Overcoat of Clay.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d977\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBesides this May We know There is Another -- How fair Our Speculations of the Foreigner!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSome know Him whom We knew -- Sweet Wonder -- A Nature be Where Saints, and our plain going Neighbor Keep May!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d978\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt bloomed and dropt, a Single Noon -- The Flower -- distinct and Red -- I, passing, thought another Noon Another in its stead\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWill equal glow, and thought no More But came another Day To find the Species disappeared -- The Same Locality --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Sun in place -- no other fraud On Nature's perfect Sum -- Had I but lingered Yesterday -- Was my retrieveless blame --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMuch Flowers of this and further Zones Have perished in my Hands For seeking its Resemblance -- But unapproached it stands --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe single Flower of the Earth That I, in passing by Unconscious was -- Great Nature's Face Passed infinite by Me --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d979\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThis Merit hath the worst -- It cannot be again -- When Fate hath taunted last And thrown Her furthest Stone --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Maimed may pause, and breathe, And glance securely round -- The Deer attracts no further Than it resists -- the Hound --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d980\u13\'0d\u13\'0dPurple -- is fashionable twice -- This season of the year, And when a soul perceives itself To be an Emperor.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d981 As Sleigh Bells seem in summer Or Bees, at Christmas show -- So fairy -- so fictitious The individuals do Repealed from observation -- A Party that we knew -- More distant in an instant Than Dawn in Timbuctoo.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d982\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNo Other can reduce Our mortal Consequence Like the remembering it be nought A Period from hence But Contemplation for Contemporaneous Nought Our Single Competition Jehovah's Estimate.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d983\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIdeals are the Fairly Oil With which we help the Wheel But when the Vital Axle turns The Eye rejects the Oil.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d984\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Tis Anguish grander than Delight 'Tis Resurrection Pain - The meeting Bands of smitten Face We questioned to, again.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Tis Transport wild as thrills the Graves When Cerements let go And Creatures clad in Miracle Go up by Two and Two. The Missing All -- prevented Me From missing minor Things. If nothing larger than a World's Departure from a Hinge -- Or Sun's extinction, be observed -- 'Twas not so large that I Could lift my Forehead from my work For Curiosity.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d986\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA narrow Fellow in the Grass Occasionally rides -- You may have met Him -- did you not His notice sudden is --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Grass divides as with a Comb -- A spotted shaft is seen - And then it closes at your feet And opens further on --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHe likes a Boggy Acre A Floor too cool for Corn -- Yet when