ted into place --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI dwelt too low that any seek -- Too shy, that any blame -- A Phoebe makes a little print Upon the Floors of Fame --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1010\u13\'0d\u13\'0dUp Life's Hill with my my little Bundle If I prove it steep -- If a Discouragement withhold me -- If my newest step\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOlder feel than the Hope that prompted -- Spotless be from blame Heart that proposed as Heart that accepted Homelessness, for Home -- She rose as high as His Occasion Then sought the Dust -- And lower lay in low Westminster For Her brief Crest --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1012\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhich is best? Heaven -- Or only Heaven to come With that old Codicil of Doubt? I cannot help esteem\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe "Bird within the Hand" Superior to the one The "Bush" may yield me Or may not Too late to choose again.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1013\u13\'0d\u13\'0dToo scanty 'twas to die for you, The merest Greek could that. The living, Sweet, is costlier -- I offer even that --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Dying, is a trifle, past, But living, this include The dying multifold -- without The Respite to be dead.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1014\u13\'0d\u13\'0dDid We abolish Frost The Summer would not cease -- If Seasons perish or prevail Is optional with Us --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1015\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWere it but Me that gained the Height -- Were it but They, that failed! How many things the Dying play Might they but live, they would!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1016\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Hills in Purple syllables The Day's Adventures tell To little Groups of Continents Just going Home from School.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1017\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo die -- without the Dying And live -- without the Life This is the hardest Miracle Propounded to Belief.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1018\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWho saw no Sunrise cannot say The Countenance 'twould be. Who guess at seeing, guess at loss Of the Ability.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Emigrant of Light, it is Afflicted for the Day. The Blindness that beheld and blest -- And could not find its Eye. My Season's furthest Flower -- I tenderer commend Because I found Her Kinsmanless, A Grace without a Friend.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1020\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTrudging to Eden, looking backward, I met Somebody's little Boy Asked him his name -- He lisped me "Trotwood" -- Lady, did He belong to thee?\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWould it comfort -- to know I met him -- And that He didn't look afraid? I couldn't weep -- for so many smiling New Acquaintance -- this Baby made --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1021\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFar from Love the Heavenly Father Leads the Chosen Child, Oftener through Realm of Briar Than the Meadow mild.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOftener by the Claw of Dragon Than the Hand of Friend Guides the Little One predestined To the Native Land.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1022\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI knew that I had gained And yet I knew not how By Diminution it was not But Discipline unto A Rigor unrelieved Except by the Content Another bear its Duplicate In other Continent.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1023\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt rises -- passes -- on our South Inscribes a simple Noon -- Cajoles a Moment with the Spires And infinite is gone --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1024\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSo large my Will The little that I may Embarrasses Like gentle infamy --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAffront to Him For whom the Whole were small Affront to me Who know His Meed of all.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dEarth at the best Is but a scanty Toy -- Bought, carried Home To Immortality.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt looks so small We chiefly wonder then At our Conceit In purchasing.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1025\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Products of my Farm are these Sufficient for my Own And here and there a Benefit Unto a Neighbor's Bin.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWith Us, 'tis Harvest all the Year For when the Frosts begin We just reverse the Zodiac And fetch the Acres in.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1026\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Dying need but little, Dear, A Glass of Water's all, A Flower's unobtrusive Face To punctuate the Wall,\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Fan, perhaps, a Friend's Regret And Certainty that one No color in the Rainbow Perceive, when you are gone.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1027\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMy Heart upon a little Plate Her Palate to delight A Berry or a Bun, would be, Might it an Apricot!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1028\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Twas my one Glory -- Let it be Remembered I was owned of Thee --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1029 Nor Mountain hinder Me Nor Sea -- Who's Baltic -- Who's Cordillera?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1030\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThat Such have died enable Us The tranquiller to die -- That Such have lived, Certificate for Immortality.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1031\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFate slew Him, but He did not drop -- She felled -- He did not fall -- Impaled Him on Her fiercest stakes -- He neutralized them all --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dShe stung Him -- sapped His firm Advance -- But when Her Worst was done And He -- unmoved regarded Her -- Acknowledged Him a Man.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1032\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWho is the East? The Yellow Man Who may be Purple if He can That carries in the Sun.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWho is the West? The Purple Man Who may be Yellow if He can That lets Him out again. Said Death to Passion "Give of thine an Acre unto me." Said Passion, through contracting Breaths "A Thousand Times Thee Nay."\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBore Death from Passion All His East He -- sovereign as the Sun Resituated in the West And the Debate was done.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1034\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHis Bill an Auger is His Head, a Cap and Frill He laboreth at every Tree A Worm, His utmost Goal.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1035\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBee! I'm expecting you! Was saying Yesterday To Somebody you know That you were due --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Frogs got Home last Week -- Are settled, and at work -- Birds, mostly back -- The Clover warm and thick --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dYou'll get my Letter by The seventeenth; Reply Or better, be with me -- Yours, Fly. Satisfaction -- is the Agent Of Satiety -- Want -- a quiet Commissary For Infinity.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo possess, is past the instant We achieve the Joy -- Immortality contented Were Anomaly.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1037\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHere, where the Daisies fit my Head 'Tis easiest to lie And every Grass that plays outside Is sorry, some, for me.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhere I am not afraid to go I may confide my Flower -- Who was not Enemy of Me Will gentle be, to Her.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNor separate, Herself and Me By Distances become -- A single Bloom we constitute Departed, or at Home --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1038\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHer little Parasol to lift And once to let it down Her whole Responsibility -- To imitate be Mine.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Summer further I must wear, Content if Nature's Drawer Present me from sepulchral Crease As blemishless, as Her.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1039\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI heard, as if I had no Ear Until a Vital Word Came all the way from Life to me And then I knew I heard.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI saw, as if my Eye were on Another, till a Thing And now I know 'twas Light, because It fitted them, came in.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI dwelt, as if Myself, were out, My Body but within Until a Might detected me And set my kernel in.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd Spirit turned unto the Dust "Old Friend, thou knowest me," And Time went out to tell the News And met Eternity.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1040\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNot so the infinite Relations -- Below Division is Adhesion's forfeit -- On High Affliction but a Speculation -- And Woe A Fallacy, a Figment, We knew --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1041\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSomewhat, to hope for, Be it ne'er so far Is Capital against Despair --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSomewhat, to suffer, Be it ne'er so keen -- If terminable, may be borne. Spring comes on the World -- I sight the Aprils -- Hueless to me until thou come As, till the Bee Blossoms stand negative,}
