Touched to Conditions By a Hum.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1043\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLest this be Heaven indeed An Obstacle is given That always gauges a Degree Between Ourself and Heaven.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1044\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Sickness of this World it most occasions When Best Men die. A Wishfulness their far Condition To occupy.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Chief indifference, as Foreign A World must be Themselves forsake -- contented, For Deity.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1045\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNature rarer uses Yellow Than another Hue. Saves she all of that for Sunsets Prodigal of Blue Spending Scarlet, like a Woman Yellow she affords Only scantly and selectly Like a Lover's Words.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1046\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI've dropped my Brain -- My Soul is numb -- The Veins that used to run Stop palsied -- 'tis Paralysis Done perfecter on stone\u13\'0d\u13\'0dVitality is Carved and cool. My nerve in Marble lies - A Breathing Woman Yesterday -- Endowed with Paradise.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNot dumb -- I had a sort that moved -- A Sense that smote and stirred -- Instincts for Dance -- a caper part -- An Aptitude for Bird --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWho wrought Carrara in me And chiselled all my tune Were it a Witchcraft -- were it Death -- I've still a chance to strain\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo Being, somewhere -- Motion -- Breath -- Though Centuries beyond, And every limit a Decade -- I'll shiver, satisfied.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1047\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Opening and the Close Of Being, are alike Or differ, if they do, As Bloom upon a Stalk.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThat from an equal Seed Unto an equal Bud Go parallel, perfected In that they have decayed.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1048\u13\'0d\u13\'0dReportless Subjects, to the Quick Continual addressed - But foreign as the Dialect Of Danes, unto the rest.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dReportless Measures, to the Ear Susceptive -- stimulus - But like an Oriental Tale To others, fabulous --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1049\u13\'0d\u13\'0dPain has but one Acquaintance And that is Death -- Each one unto the other Society enough.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dPain is the Junior Party By just a Second's right -- Death tenderly assists Him And then absconds from Sight.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1050\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAs willing lid o'er weary eye The Evening on the Day leans Till of all our nature's House Remains but Balcony\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1051 I cannot meet the Spring unmoved -- I feel the old desire -- A Hurry with a lingering, mixed, A Warrant to be fair --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Competition in my sense With something hid in Her -- And as she vanishes, Remorse I saw no more of Her.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1052\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI never saw a Moor -- I never saw the Sea -- Yet know I how the Heather looks And what a Billow be.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI never spoke with God Nor visited in Heaven -- Yet certain am I of the spot As if the Checks were given --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1053\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt was a quiet way -- He asked if I was his -- I made no answer of the Tongue But answer of the Eyes -- And then He bore me on Before this mortal noise With swiftness, as of Chariots And distance, as of Wheels. This World did drop away As Acres from the feet Of one that leaneth from Balloon Upon an Ether street. The Gulf behind was not, The Continents were new -- Eternity it was before Eternity was due. No Seasons were to us -- It was not Night nor Morn -- But Sunrise stopped upon the place And fastened it in Dawn.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1054\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNot to discover weakness is The Artifice of strength - Impregnability inheres As much through Consciousness\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOf faith of others in itself As Pyramidal Nerve Behind the most unconscious clock What skilful Pointers move --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1055\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Soul should always stand ajar That if the Heaven inquire He will not be obliged to wait Or shy of troubling Her\u13\'0d\u13\'0dDepart, before the Host have slid The Bolt unto the Door -- To search for the accomplished Guest, Her Visitor, no more --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1056\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThere is a Zone whose even Years No Solstice interrupt -- Whose Sun constructs perpetual Noon Whose perfect Seasons wait --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhose Summer set in Summer, till The Centuries of June And Centuries of August cease And Consciousness -- is Noon. 1057\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI had a daily Bliss I half indifferent viewed Till sudden I perceived it stir -- It grew as I pursued\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTill when around a Height It wasted from my sight Increased beyond my utmost scope I learned to estimate.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1058\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBloom -- is Result -- to meet a Flower And casually glance Would scarcely cause one to suspect The minor Circumstance\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAssisting in the Bright Affair So intricately done Then offered as a Butterfly To the Meridian --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo pack the Bud -- oppose the Worm -- Obtain its right of Dew -- Adjust the Heat -- elude the Wind -Escape the prowling Bee\u13\'0d\u13\'0dGreat Nature not to disappoint Awaiting Her that Day -- To be a Flower, is profound Responsibility --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1059\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSang from the Heart, Sire, Dipped my Beak in it, If the Tune drip too much Have a tint too Red\u13\'0d\u13\'0dPardon the Cochineal -Suffer the Vermillion -- Death is the Wealth Of the Poorest Bird.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBear with the Ballad -- Awkward -- faltering -- Death twists the strings -'Twasn't my blame --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dPause in your Liturgies -Wait your Chorals -- While I repeat your Hallowed name --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1060\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAir has no Residence, no Neighbor, No Ear, no Door, No Apprehension of Another Oh, Happy Air!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dEthereal Guest at e'en an Outcast's Pillow -- Essential Host, in Life's faint, wailing Inn, Later than Light thy Consciousness accost me Till it depart, persuading Mine --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1061\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThree Weeks passed since I had seen Her -- Some Disease had vext 'Twas with Text and Village Singing I beheld Her next\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd a Company -- our pleasure To discourse alone -- Gracious now to me as any -- Gracious unto none --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBorne without dissent of Either To the Parish night -- Of the Separated Parties Which be out of sight?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1062\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHe scanned it -- staggered -- Dropped the Loop To Past or Period -- Caught helpless at a sense as if His Mind were going blind --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dGroped up, to see if God was there -- Groped backward at Himself Caressed a Trigger absently And wandered out of Life.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1063\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAshes denote that Fire was -- Revere the Grayest Pile For the Departed Creature's sake That hovered there awhile --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFire exists the first in light And then consolidates Only the Chemist can disclose Into what Carbonates.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1064\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo help our Bleaker Parts Salubrious Hours are given Which if they do not fir for Earth Drill silently for Heaven -- 1065\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLet down the Bars, Oh Death -- The tired Flocks come in Whose bleating ceases to repeat Whose wandering is done --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThine is the stillest night Thine the securest Fold Too near Thou art for seeking Thee Too tender, to be told.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1066 Fame's Boys and Girls, who never die And are too seldom born -- 1067\u13\'0d\u13\'0dExcept the smaller size No lives are round -- These -- hurry to a sphere And show and end -- The larger -- slower grow And later hang -- The Summers of Hesperides Are long.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1068\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFurther in Summer than the Birds Pathetic from the Grass A minor Nation celebrates Its unobtrusive Mass.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNo Ordinance be seen So gradual the Grace A pensive Custom it becomes Enlarging Loneliness.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAntiquest felt at Noon When August burning low Arise this spectral Canticle Repose to typify\u13\'0d\u13\'0dRemit as yet no Grace No Furrow on the Glow Yet a Druidic Difference Enhances Nature now\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1069\u13\'0d\u13\'0dParadise is of the option. Whosoever will Own in Eden notwithstanding Adam and Repeal.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1070\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo undertake is to achieve Be Undertaking blent With fortitude of obstacle And toward encouragement\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThat fine Suspicion, Natures must Permitted to revere Departed Standards and the few Criterion Sources here\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1071\u13\'0d\u13\'0dPerception of an object costs Precise the Object's loss -- Perception in itself a Gain Replying to its Price --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Object Absolute -- is nought -Perception sets it fair And then upbraids a Perfectness That situates so far --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1072\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTitle divine -- is mine! The Wife -- without the Sign! Acute Degree -- conferred on me -- Empress of Calvary! Royal -- all but the Crown! Betrothed -- without the swoon God sends us Women -- When you -- hold -- Garnet to Garnet -- Gold -- to Gold -- Born -- Bridalled -- Shrouded -- In a Day -- Tri Victory "My Husband" -- women say -- Stroking the Melody -- Is this -- the way?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1073\u13\'0d\u13\'0dExperiment to me Is every one I meet If it contain a Kernel? The Figure of a Nut\u13\'0d\u13\'0dPresents upon a Tree Equally plausibly, But Meat within, is requisite To Squirrels, and to Me.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1074\u13\'0d\u13\'0dCount not that far that can be had, Though sunset lie between -- Nor that adjacent, that beside, Is further than the sun.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1075\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Sky is low -- the Clouds are mean. A Travelling Flake of Snow Across a Barn or through a Rut Debates if it will go --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Narrow Wind complains all Day How some one treated him Nature, like Us is sometimes caught Without her Diadem.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1076\u13\'0d\u13\'0dJust Once! Oh least Request! Could Adamant refuse So small a Grace So scanty put, Such agonizing terms? Would not a God of Flint Be conscious of a sigh As down His Heaven dropt remote "Just Once" Sweet Deity?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1077\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThese are the Signs to Nature's Inns -- Her invitation broad To Whosoever famishing To taste her mystic Bread --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThese are the rites of Nature's House -- The Hospitality That opens with an equal width To Beggar and to Bee For Sureties of her staunch Estate Her undecaying Cheer The Purple in the East is set And in the North, the Star --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1078\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Bustle in a House The Morning after Death Is solemnest of industries Enacted upon Earth --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Sweeping up the Heart And putting Love away We shall not want to use again Until Eternity.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1079\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Sun went down -- no Man looked on -- The Earth and I, alone, Were present at the Majesty -- He triumphed, and went on --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Sun went up -- no Man looked on -- The Earth and I and One A nameless Bird -- a Stranger Were Witness for the Crown --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1080\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhen they come back -- if Blossoms do -- I always feel a doubt If Blossoms can be born again When once the Art is out --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhen they begin, if Robins may, I always had a fear I did not tell, it was their last Experiment Last Year,\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhen it is May, if May return, Had nobody a pang Lest in a Face so beautiful He might not look again?\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIf I am there -- One does not know What Party -- One may be Tomorrow, but if I am there I take back all I say --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1081\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSuperiority to Fate Is difficult to gain 'Tis not conferred of Any But possible to earn\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA pittance at a time Until to Her surprise The Soul with strict economy Subsist till Paradise.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1082\u13\'0d\u13\'0dRevolution}
