again And it was out of sight -\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1121\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTime does go on -- I tell it gay to those who suffer now -- They shall survive -- There is a sun -- They don't believe it now --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1122\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Tis my first night beneath the Sun If I should spend it here -- Above him is too low a height For his Barometer Who Airs of expectation breathes And takes the Wind at prime -- But Distance his Delights confides To those who visit him -- 1123\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA great Hope fell You heard no noise The Ruin was within Oh cunning wreck that told no tale And let no Witness in\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe mind was built for mighty Freight For dread occasion planned How often foundering at Sea Ostensibly, on Land\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA not admitting of the wound Until it grew so wide That all my Life had entered it And there were troughs beside\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA closing of the simple lid That opened to the sun Until the tender Carpenter Perpetual nail it down -\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1124\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHad we known the Ton she bore We had helped the terror But she straighter walked for Freight So be hers the error --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1125\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOh Sumptuous moment Slower go That I may gloat on thee -- 'Twill never be the same to starve Now I abundance see -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhich was to famish, then or now -- The difference of Day Ask him unto the Gallows led -- With morning in the sky --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1126\u13\'0d\u13\'0dShall I take thee, the Poet said To the propounded word? Be stationed with the Candidates Till I have finer tried --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Poet searched Philology And when about to ring For the suspended Candidate There came unsummoned in --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThat portion of the Vision The Word applied to fill Not unto nomination The Cherubim reveal --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1127 Soft as the massacre of Suns By Evening's Sabres slain 1128\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThese are the Nights that Beetles love -- From Eminence remote Drives ponderous perpendicular His figure intimate The terror of the Children The merriment of men Depositing his Thunder He hoists abroad again - A Bomb upon the Ceiling Is an improving thing -- It keeps the nerves progressive Conjecture flourishing - Too dear the Summer evening Without discreet alarm -- Supplied by Entomology With its remaining charm --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1129\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTell all the Truth but tell it slant -- Success in Circuit lies Too bright for our infirm Delight The Truth's superb surprise\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAs Lightning to the Children eased With explanation kind The Truth must dazzle gradually Or every man be blind -\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1130\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThat odd old man is dead a year -- We miss his stated Hat. 'Twas such an evening bright and stiff His faded lamp went out.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWho miss his antiquated Wick -- Are any hoar for him? Waits any indurated mate His wrinkled coming Home?\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOh Life, begun in fluent Blood And consummated dull! Achievement contemplating thee -- Feels transitive and cool.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1131\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Merchant of the Picturesque A Counter has and sales But is within or negative Precisely as the calls - To Children he is small in price And large in courtesy -- It suits him better than a check Their artless currency -- Of Counterfeits he is so shy Do one advance so near As to behold his ample flight --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1132\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe smouldering embers blush -- Oh Hearts within the Coal Hast thou survived so many years? The smouldering embers smile -- Soft stirs the news of Light The stolid seconds glow One requisite has Fire that lasts Prometheus never knew --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1133\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Snow that never drifts -- The transient, fragrant snow That comes a single time a Year Is softly driving now --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSo thorough in the Tree At night beneath the star That it was February's Foot Experience would swear --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLike Winter as a Face We stern and former knew Repaired of all but Loneliness By Nature's Alibit --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWere every storm so spice The Value could not be -We buy with contrast -- Pang is good As near as memory --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1134\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Wind took up the Northern Things And piled them in the south -- Then gave the East unto the West And opening his mouth\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe four Divisions of the Earth Did make as to devour While everything to corners slunk Behind the awful power --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Wind -- unto his Chambers went And nature ventured out -- Her subjects scattered into place Her systems ranged about\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAgain the smoke from Dwellings rose The Day abroad was heard -- How intimate, a Tempest past The Transport of the Bird --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1135\u13\'0d\u13\'0dToo cold is this To warm with Sun -- Too stiff to bended be, To joint this Agate were a work -- Outstaring Masonry --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHow went the Agile Kernel out Contusion of the Husk Nor Rip, nor wrinkle indicate But just an Asterisk. The Frost of Death was on the Pane -- "Secure your Flower" said he. Like Sailors fighting with a Leak We fought Mortality.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOur passive Flower we held to Sea -- To Mountain -- To the Sun -- Yet even on his Scarlet shelf To crawl the Frost begun --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWe pried him back Ourselves we wedged Himself and her between, Yet easy as the narrow Snake He forked his way along\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTill all her helpless beauty bent And then our wrath begun -- We hunted him to his Ravine We chased him to his Den --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWe hated Death and hated Life And nowhere was to go -- Than Sea and continent there is A larger -- it is Woe --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1137\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe duties of the Wind are few, To cast the ships, at Sea, Establish March, the Floods escort, And usher Liberty.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe pleasures of the Wind are broad, To dwell Extent among, Remain, or wander, Speculate, or Forests entertain.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe kinsmen of the Wind are Peaks Azof -- the Equinox, Also with Bird and Asteroid A bowing intercourse.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe limitations of the Wind Do he exist, or die, Too wise he seems for Wakelessness, However, know not i.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1138\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Spider sewed at Night Without a Light Upon an Arc of White.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIf Ruff it was of Dame Or Shroud of Gnome Himself himself inform.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOf Immortality His Strategy Was Physiognomy.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1139\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHer sovereign People Nature knows as well And is as fond of signifying As if fallible --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1140\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Day grew small, surrounded tight By early, stooping Night -- The Afternoon in Evening deep Its Yellow shortness dropt -- The Winds went out their martial ways The Leaves obtained excuse -- November hung his Granite Hat Upon a nail of Plush -- The Face we choose to miss -- Be it but for a Day As absent as a Hundred Years, When it has rode away.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1142\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Props assist the House Until the House is built And then the Props withdraw And adequate, erect, The House support itself And cease to recollect The Auger and the Carpenter -- Just such a retrospect Hath the perfected Life - A past of Plank and Nail And slowness -- then the Scaffolds drop Affirming it a Soul.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1143\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Work of Her that went, The Toil of Fellows done -- In Ovens green our Mother bakes, By Fires of the Sun.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1144\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOurselves we do inter with sweet derision. The channel of the dust who once achieves Invalidates the balm of that religion That doubts as fervently as it believes. In thy long Paradise of Light No moment will there be When I shall long for Earthly Play And mortal Company --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1146\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhen Etna basks and purrs Naples is more afraid Than when she show her Garnet Tooth -- Security is loud --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1147\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAfter a hundred years Nobody knows the Place Agony that enacted there Motionless as Peace\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWeeds triumphant ranged Strangers strolled and spelled At the lone Orthography Of the Elder Dead\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWinds of Summer Fields Recollect the way -- Instinct picking up the Key Dropped by memory --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1148\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAfter the Sun comes out How it alters the World - Waggons like messengers hurry about Yesterday is old --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAll men meet as if Each foreclosed a news -- Fresh as a Cargo from Batize Nature's qualities --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1149\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI noticed People disappeared When but a little child - Supposed they visited remote Or settled Regions wild -But did because they died A Fact withheld the little child --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1150\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHow many schemes may die In one short Afternoon Entirely unknown To those they most concern -- The man that was not lost Because by accident He varied by a Ribbon's width From his accustomed route -- The Love that would not try Because beside the Door It must be competitions Some unsuspecting Horse was tied Surveying his Despair\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1151\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSoul, take thy risk. With Death to be Were better than be not With thee Tell as a Marksman -- were forgotten Tell -- this Day endures Ruddy as that coeval Apple The Tradition bears --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFresh as Mankind that humble story Though a statelier Tale Grown in the Repetition hoary Scarcely would prevail --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTell had a son -- The ones that knew it Need not linger here -- Those who did not to Human Nature Will subscribe a Tear --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTell would not bare his Head In Presence Of the Ducal Hat -- Threatened for that with Death -- by Gessler -- Tyranny bethought\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMake of his only Boy a Target That surpasses Death - Stolid to Love's supreme entreaty Not forsook of Faith --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMercy of the Almighty begging -- Tell his Arrow sent -- God it is said replies in Person When the cry is meant --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1153\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThrough what transports of Patience I reached the stolid Bliss To breathe my Blank without thee Attest me this and this - By that bleak exultation I won as near as this Thy privilege of dying Abbreviate me this --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1154\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA full fed Rose on meals of Tint A Dinner for a Bee In process of the Noon became - Each bright Mortality The Forfeit is of Creature fair Itself, adored before Submitting for our unknown sake To be esteemed no more --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1155\u13\'0d\u13\'0dDistance -- is not the Realm of Fox Nor by Relay of Bird Abated -- Distance is Until thyself, Beloved.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1156\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLest any doubt that we are glad that they were born Today Whose having lived is held by us in noble Holiday Without the date, like Consciousness or Immortality --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1157\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSome Days retired from the rest In soft distinction lie The Day that a Companion came Or was obliged to die Best Witchcraft is Geometry To the magician's mind -His ordinary acts are feats To thinking of mankind.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1159\u13\'0d\u13\'0dGreat Streets of silence led away To Neighborhoods of Pause -- Here was no Notice -- no Dissent No Universe -- no laws --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBy Clocks, 'twas Morning, and for Night The Bells at Distance called -- But Epoch had no basis here For Period exhaled.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1160\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHe is alive, this morning}
