-- He is alive -- and awake -- Birds are resuming for Him -- Blossoms -- dress for His Sake. Bees -- to their Loaves of Honey Add an Amber Crumb Him -- to regale -- Me -- Only -- Motion, and am dumb.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1161\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTrust adjust her "Peradventure" -- Phantoms entered "and not you." The Life we have is very great. The Life that we shall see Surpasses it, we know, because It is Infinity. But when all Space has been beheld And all Dominion shown The smallest Human Heart's extent Reduces it to none.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1163\u13\'0d\u13\'0dGod made no act without a cause, Nor heart without an aim, Our inference is premature, Our premises to blame.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1164\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWere it to be the last How infinite would be What we did not suspect was marked -- Our final interview.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1165\u13\'0d\u13\'0dContained in this short Life Are magical extents The soul returning soft at night To steal securer thence\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAs Children strictest kept Turn soonest to the sea Whose nameless Fathoms slink away Beside infinity Of Paul and Silas it is said There were in Prison laid But when they went to take them out They were not there instead.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSecurity the same insures To our assaulted Minds -- The staple must be optional That an Immortal binds.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1167\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAlone and in a Circumstance Reluctant to be told A spider on my reticence Assiduously crawled\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd so much more at Home than I Immediately grew I felt myself a visitor And hurriedly withdrew\u13\'0d\u13\'0dRevisiting my late abode With articles of claim I found it quietly assumed As a Gymnasium Where Tax asleep and Title off The inmates of the Air Perpetual presumption took As each were special Heir -- If any strike me on the street I can return the Blow --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIf any take my property According to the Law The Statute is my Learned friend But what redress can be For an offense nor here nor there So not in Equity -- That Larceny of time and mind The marrow of the Day By spider, or forbid it Lord That I should specify.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1168\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAs old as Woe -- How old is that? Some eighteen thousand years -- As old as Bliss How old is that They are of equal years\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTogether chiefest they ard found But seldom side by side From neither of them tho' he try Can Human nature hide\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1169 Lest they should come -- is all my fear When sweet incarcerated here 1170\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNature affects to be sedate Upon occasion, grand But let our observation shut Her practices extend\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo Necromancy and the Trades Remote to understand Behold our spacious Citizen Unto a Juggler turned -- On the World you colored Morning painted rose -Idle his Vermillion Aimlessly crept the Glows Over Realms of Orchards I the Day before Conquered with the Robin -- Misery, how fair Till your wrinkled Finger Shored the sun away Midnight's awful Pattern In the Goods of Day --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1172\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Clouds their Backs together laid The North begun to push The Forests galloped till they fell The Lightning played like mice\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Thunder crumbled like a stuff How good to be in Tombs Where Nature's Temper cannot reach Nor missile ever comes\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1173\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Lightning is a yellow Fork From Tables in the sky By inadvertent fingers dropt The awful Cutlery\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOf mansions never quite disclosed And never quite concealed The Apparatus of the Dark To ignorance revealed.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1174\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThere's the Battle of Burgoyne -- Over, every Day, By the Time that Man and Beast Put their work away "Sunset" sounds majestic -- But that solemn War Could you comprehend it You would chastened stare --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1175\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWe like a Hairbreadth 'scape It tingles in the Mind Far after Act or Accident Like paragraphs of Wind\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIf we had ventured less The Breeze were not so fine That reaches to our utmost Hair Its Tentacles divine.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1176\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWe never know how high we are Till we are asked to rise And then if we are true to plan Our statures touch the skies --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Heroism we recite Would be a normal thing Did not ourselves the Cubits warp For fear to be a King --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1177\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA prompt -- executive Bird is the Jay -- Bold as a Bailiff's Hymn -- Brittle and Brief in quality -- Warrant in every line -- Sitting a Bough like a Brigadier Confident and straight - Much is the mien of him in March As a Magistrate --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1178\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMy God -- He sees thee -- Shine thy best -- Fling up thy Balls of Gold Till every Cubit play with thee And every Crescent hold -- Elate the Acre at his feet -- Upon his Atom swim -- Oh Sun -- but just a Second's right In thy long Race with him!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1179\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOf so divine a Loss We enter but the Gain, Indemnity for Loneliness That such a Bliss has been.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1180\u13\'0d\u13\'0d"Remember me" implored the Thief! Oh Hospitality! My Guest "Today in Paradise" I give thee guaranty.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThat Courtesy will fair remain When the Delight is Dust With which we cite this mightiest case Of compensated Trust.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOf all we are allowed to hope But Affidavit stands That this was due where most we fear Be unexpected Friends.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1181\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhen I hoped I feared -- Since I hoped I dared Everywhere alone As a Church remain -- Spectre cannot harm -- Serpent cannot charm -- He deposes Doom Who hath suffered him --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1182\u13\'0d\u13\'0dRemembrance has a Rear and Front -- 'Tis something like a House -- It has a Garret also For Refuse and the Mouse.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBesides the deepest Cellar That ever Mason laid -Look to it by its Fathoms Ourselves be not pursued --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1183\u13\'0d\u13\'0dStep lightly on this narrow spot -- The broadest Land that grows Is not so ample as the Breast These Emerald Seams enclose.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dStep lofty, for this name be told As far as Cannon dwell Or Flag subsist or Fame export Her deathless Syllable. The Days that we can spare Are those a Function die Or Friend or Nature -- stranded then In our Economy\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOur Estimates a Scheme -- Our Ultimates a Sham -- We let go all of Time without Arithmetic of him --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1185\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA little Dog that wags his tail And knows no other joy Of such a little Dog am I Reminded by a Boy\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWho gambols all the living Day Without an earthly cause Because he is a little Boy I honestly suppose --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Cat that in the Corner dwells Her martial Day forgot The Mouse but a Tradition now Of her desireless Lot\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnother class remind me Who neither please nor play But not to make a "bit of noise" Beseech each little Boy --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1186\u13\'0d\u13\'0dToo few the mornings be, Too scant the nights. No lodging can be had For the delights That come to earth to stay, But no apartment find And ride away.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1187\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOh Shadow on the Grass, Art thou a Step or not? Go make thee fair my Candidate My nominated Heart -- Oh Shadow on the Grass While I delay to guess Some other thou wilt consecrate -- Oh Unelected Face --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1188\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Twas fighting for his Life he was -- That sort accomplish well -- The Ordnance of Vitality Is frugal of its Ball.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt aims once -- kills once -- conquers once -- There is no second War In that Campaign inscrutable Of the Interior.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1189\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Voice that stands for Floods to me Is sterile borne to some -- The Face that makes the Morning mean Glows impotent on them --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhat difference in Substance lies That what is Sum to me By other Financiers be deemed Exclusive Property! The Sun and Fog contested The Government of Day -- The Sun took down his Yellow Whip And drove the Fog away --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1191\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe pungent atom in the Air Admits of no debate -- All that is named of Summer Days Relinquished our Estate --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFor what Department of Delight As positive are we As Limit of Dominion Or Dams -- of Ecstasy --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1192\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAn honest Tear Is durabler than Bronze -- This Cenotaph May each that dies --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dReared by itself -- No Deputy suffice -- Gratitude bears When Obelisk decays\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1193\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAll men for Honor hardest work But are not known to earn -- Paid after they have ceased to work In Infamy or Urn --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1194\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSomehow myself survived the Night And entered with the Day -- That it be saved the Saved suffice Without the Formula.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHenceforth I take my living place As one commuted led -- A Candidate for Morning Chance But dated with the Dead.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1195\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhat we see we know somewhat Be it but a little -- What we don't surmise we do Though it shows so fickle\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI shall vote for Lands with Locks Granted I can pick 'em -- Transport's doubtful Dividend Patented by Adam.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1196\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo make Routine a Stimulus Remember it can cease -- Capacity to Terminate Is a Specific Grace -- Of Retrospect the Arrow That power to repair Departed with the Torment Become, alas, more fair -- I should not dare to be so sad So many Years again - A Load is first impossible When we have put it down --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Superhuman then withdraws And we who never saw The Giant at the other side Begin to perish now.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1198\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA soft Sea washed around the House A Sea of Summer Air And rose and fell the magic Planks That sailed without a care -- For Captain was the Butterfly For Helmsman was the Bee And an entire universe For the delighted crew.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1199\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAre Friends Delight or Pain? Could Bounty but remain Riches were good --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut if they only stay Ampler to fly away Riches are sad.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dPoems No. 1200-1299\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1200\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBecause my Brook is fluent I know 'tis dry -- Because my Brook is silent It is the Sea --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd startled at its rising I try to flee To where the Strong assure me Is "no more Sea" --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1201\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSo I pull my Stockings off Wading in the Water For the Disobedience' Sake Boy that lived for "or'ter"\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWent to Heaven perhaps at Death And perhaps he didn't Moses wasn't fairly used -- Ananias wasn't --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1202\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Frost was never seen -- If met, too rapid passed, Or in too unsubstantial Team -- The Flowers notice first\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Stranger hovering round A Symptom of alarm In Villages remotely set But search effaces him\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTill some retrieveless Night Our Vigilance at waste The Garden gets the only shot That never could be traced.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dUnproved is much we know -- Unknown the worst we fear -- Of Strangers is the Earth the Inn Of Secrets is the Air --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo analyze perhaps A Philip would prefer But Labor vaster than myself I find it to infer.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1203\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Past is such a curious Creature To look her in the Face A Transport may receipt us Or a Disgrace --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dUnarmed if any meet her I charge him fly Her faded Ammunition Might yet reply.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1204\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhatever it is --}
