il of the Bold Hoary the Fruition But the Sea is old\u13\'0d\u13\'0dEdifice of Ocean Thy tumultuous Rooms Suit me at a venture Better than the Tombs\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1218\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLet my first Knowing be of thee With morning's warming Light -- And my first Fearing, lest Unknowns Engulf thee in the night -\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1219\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNow I knew I lost her -Not that she was gone -- But Remoteness travelled On her Face and Tongue.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAlien, though adjoining As a Foreign Race -- Traversed she though pausing Latitudeless Place.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dElements Unaltered -- Universe the same But Love's transmigration -- Somehow this had come --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHenceforth to remember Nature took the Day I had paid so much for -- His is Penury Not who toils for Freedom Or for Family But the Restitution Of Idolatry.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1220\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOf Nature I shall have enough When I have entered these Entitled to a Bumble bee's Familiarities.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1221\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSome we see no more, Tenements of Wonder Occupy to us though perhaps to them Simpler are the Days than the Supposition Leave us to presume\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThat oblique Belief which we call Conjecture Grapples with a Theme stubborn as Sublime Able as the Dust to equip its feature Adequate as Drums To enlist the Tomb.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1222\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Riddle we can guess We speedily despise -- Not anything is stale so long As Yesterday's surprise --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1223\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWho goes to dine must take his Feast Or find the Banquet mean -- The Table is not laid without Till it is laid within.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFor Pattern is the Mind bestowed That imitating her Our most ignoble Services Exhibit worthier.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1224\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLike Trains of Cars on Tracks of Plush I hear the level Bee -- A Jar across the Flowers goes Their Velvet Masonry --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWithstands until the sweet Assault Their Chivalry consumes -- While He, victorious tilts away To vanquish other Blooms.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1225 Its Hour with itself The Spirit never shows. What Terror would enthrall the Street Could Countenance disclose\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Subterranean Freight The Cellars of the Soul -- Thank God the loudest Place he made Is license to be still.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1226\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Popular Heart is a Cannon first -Subsequent a Drum -- Bells for an Auxiliary And an Afterward of Rum --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNot a Tomorrow to know its name Nor a Past to stare -- Ditches for Realms and a Trip to Jail For a Souvenir --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1227\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMy Triumph lasted till the Drums Had left the Dead alone And then I dropped my Victory And chastened stole along To where the finished Faces Conclusion turned on me And then I hated Glory And wished myself were They.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhat is to be is best descried When it has also been - Could Prospect taste of Retrospect The tyrannies of Men Were Tenderer -- diviner The Transitive toward. A Bayonet's contrition Is nothing to the Dead.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1228\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSo much of Heaven has gone from Earth That there must be a Heaven If only to enclose the Saints To Affidavit given.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Missionary to the Mole Must prove there is a Sky Location doubtless he would plead But what excuse have I?\u13\'0d\u13\'0dToo much of Proof affronts Belief The Turtle will not try Unless you leave him -- then return And he has hauled away.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1229\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBecause He loves Her We will pry and see if she is fair What difference is on her Face From Features others wear.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt will not harm her magic pace That we so far behind - Her Distances propitiate As Forests touch the Wind\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNot hoping for his notice vast But nearer to adore 'Tis Glory's far sufficiency That makes our trying poor.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1230\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt came at last but prompter Death Had occupied the House -- His pallid Furniture arranged And his metallic Peace --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOh faithful Frost that