Soonest to share But for the Greed of him -- Boasting my Premium -- Basking in Bethleem Ere I be there --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1238\u13\'0d\u13\'0dPower is a familiar growth -- Not foreign -- not to be -- Beside us like a bland Abyss In every company -- Escape it -- there is but a chance -When consciousness and clay Lean forward for a final glance -- Disprove that and you may -- Risk is the Hair that holds the Tun Seductive in the Air -- That Tun is hollow -- but the Tun -- With Hundred Weights -- to spare -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dToo ponderous to suspect the snare Espies that fickle chair And seats itself to be let go By that perfidious Hair -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe "foolish Tun" the Critics say -- While that delusive Hair Persuasive as Perdition, Decoys its Traveller.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1240\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Beggar at the Door for Fame Were easily supplied But Bread is that Diviner thing Disclosed to be denied\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1241\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Lilac is an ancient shrub But ancienter than that The Firmamental Lilac Upon the Hill tonight -- The Sun subsiding on his Course Bequeaths this final Plant To Contemplation -- not to Touch -- The Flower of Occident. Of one Corolla is the West -- The Calyx is the Earth -- The Capsules burnished Seeds the Stars The Scientist of Faith His research has but just begun -Above his synthesis The Flora unimpeachable}
