face.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1252\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLike Brooms of Steel The Snow and Wind Had swept the Winter Street -- The House was hooked The Sun sent out Faint Deputies of Heat -- Where rode the Bird The Silence tied His ample -- plodding Steed The Apple in the Cellar snug Was all the one that played. Had this one Day not been. Or could it cease to be How smitten, how superfluous, Were every other Day!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLest Love should value less What Loss would value more Had it the stricken privilege, It cherishes before.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1254\u13\'0d\u13\'0dElijah's Wagon knew no thill Was innocent of Wheel Elijah's horses as unique As was his vehicle --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dElijah's journey to portray Expire with him the skill Who justified Elijah In feats inscrutable --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1255\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLonging is like the Seed That wrestles in the Ground, Believing if it intercede It shall at length be found.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Hour, and the Clime -- Each Circumstance unknown, What Constancy must be achieved Before it see the Sun! Not any higher stands the Grave For Heroes than for Men -- Not any nearer for the Child Than numb Three Score and Ten --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThis latest Leisure equal lulls The Beggar and his Queen Propitiate this Democrat A Summer's Afternoon --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1257\u13\'0d\u13\'0dDominion lasts until obtained -- Possession just as long -- But these -- endowing as they flit Eternally belong.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHow everlasting are the Lips Known only to the Dew -- These are the Brides of permanence Supplanting me and you.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1258\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWho were "the Father and the Son" We pondered when a child, And what had they to do with us And when portentous told\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWith inference appalling By Childhood fortified We thought, at least they are no worse Than they have been described.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWho are "the Father and the Son" Did we demand Today "The Father and the Son" himself Would doubtless specify --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut had they the felicity When we desired to know. We better Friends had been, perhaps, Than time ensue to be -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWe start -- to learn that we believe But once -- entirely -- Belief, it does not fit so well When altered frequently --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWe blush, that Heaven if we achieve -- Event ineffable -- We shall have shunned until ashamed To own the Miracle --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1259\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Wind that rose Though not a Leaf In any Forest stirred But with itself did cold engage Beyond the Realm of Bird -- A Wind that woke a lone Delight Like Separation's Swell Restored in Arctic Confidence To the Invisible --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1260\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBecause that you are going And never coming back And I, however absolute, May overlook your Track --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBecause that Death is final, However first it be, This instant be suspended Above Mortality --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSignificance that each has lived The other to detect Discovery not God himself Could now annihilate\u13\'0d\u13\'0dEternity, Presumption The instant I perceive That you, who were Existence Yourself forgot to live --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe "Life that is" will then have been A thing I never knew -- As Paradise fictitious Until the Realm of you --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe "Life that is to be," to me, A Residence too plain Unless in my Redeemer's Face I recognize your own --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOf Immortality who doubts He may exchange with me Curtailed by your obscuring Face Of everything but He --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOf Heaven and Hell I also yield The Right to reprehend To whoso would commute this Face For his less priceless Friend.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIf "God is Love" as he admits We think that me must be Because he is a "jealous God" He tells us certainly\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIf "All is possible with" him As he besides concedes He will refund us finally Our confiscated Gods --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1261\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Word dropped careless on a Page May stimulate an eye When folded in perpetual seam The Wrinkled Maker lie\u13\'0d\u13\'0dInfection in the sentence breeds We may inhale Despair At distances of Centuries From the Malaria --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1262\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI cannot see my soul but know 'tis there Nor ever saw his house nor furniture, Who has invited me with him to dwell; But a confiding guest consult as well, What raiment honor him the most, That I be adequately dressed, For he insures to none Lest men specified adorn Procuring him perpetual drest By dating it a sudden feast.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1263\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThere is no Frigate like a Book To take us Lands away Nor any Coursers like a Page Of prancing Poetry -- This Traverse may the poorest take Without oppress of Toll - How frugal is the Chariot That bears the Human soul.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1264\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThis is the place they hoped before, Where I am hoping now. The seed of disappointment grew Within a capsule gay, Too distant to arrest the feet That walk this plank of balm -- Before them lies escapeless sea -- The way is closed they came.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1265\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe most triumphant Bird I ever knew or met Embarked upon a twig today And till Dominion set I famish to behold so eminent a sight And sang for nothing scrutable But intimate Delight. Retired, and resumed his transitive Estate -- To what delicious Accident Does finest Glory fit!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1266\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhen Memory is full Put on the perfect Lid - This Morning's finest syllable Presumptuous Evening said --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1267\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI saw that the Flake was on it But plotted with Time to dispute -- "Unchanged" I urged with a candor That cost me my honest Heart --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut "you" -- she returned with valor Sagacious of my mistake "Have altered -- Accept the pillage For the progress' sake" - 1268\u13\'0d\u13\'0dConfirming All who analyze In the Opinion fair That Eloquence is when the Heart Has not a Voice to spare --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1269\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI worked for chaff and earning Wheat Was haughty and betrayed. What right had Fields to arbitrate In matters ratified?\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI tasted Wheat and hated Chaff And thanked the ample friend -- Wisdom is more becoming viewed At distance than at hand.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1270\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIs Heaven a Physician? They say that He can heal -- But Medicine Posthumous Is unavailable -- Is Heaven an Exchequer? They speak of what we owe -- But that negotiation I'm not a Party to --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1271\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSeptember's Baccalaureate A combination is Of Crickets -- Crows -- and Retrospects And a dissembling Breeze That hints without assuming -- An Innuendo sear That makes the Heart put up its Fun And turn Philosopher.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1272\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSo proud she was to die It made us all ashamed That what we cherished, so unknown To her desire seemed -- So satisfied to go Where none of us should be Immediately -- that Anguish stooped Almost to Jealousy --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1273\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThat sacred Closet when you sweep -- Entitled "Memory" -- Select a reverential Broom -- And do it silently.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Twill be a Labor of surprise -- Besides Identity Of other Interlocutors A probability --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAugust the Dust of that Domain -- Unchallenged -- let it lie - You cannot supersede itself But it can silence you --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1274\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Bone that has no Marrow, What Ultimate for that? It is not fit for Table For Beggar or for Cat.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Bone has obligations -- A Being has the same -- A Marrowless Assembly Is culpabler than shame.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut how shall finished Creatures A function fresh obtain? Old Nicodemus' Phantom Confronting us again!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1275\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Spider as an Artist Has never been employed -- Though his surpassing Merit Is freely certified\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBy every Broom and Bridget Throughout a Christian Land -- Neglected Son of Genius I take thee by the Hand --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1276\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Twas later when the summer went Than when the Cricket came -- And yet we knew that gentle Clock Meant nought but Going Home -- 'Twas sooner when the Cricket went Than when the Winter came Yet that pathetic Pendulum Keeps esoteric Time.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1277\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhile we were fearing it, it came -- But came with less of fear Because that fearing it so long Had almost made it fair -- There is a Fitting -- a Dismay -- A Fitting -- a Despair 'Tis harder knowing it is Due Than knowing it is Here.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThey Trying on the Utmost The Morning it is new Is Terribler than wearing it A whole existence through.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1278\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Mountains stood in Haze -- The Valleys stopped below And went or waited as they liked The River and the Sky.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAt leisure was the Sun -- His interests of Fire A little from remark withdrawn -- The Twilight spoke the Spire,\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSo soft upon the Scene The Act of evening fell We felt how neighborly a Thing Was the Invisible.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1279\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Way to know the Bobolink From every other Bird Precisely as the Joy of him -- Obliged to be inferred.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOf impudent Habiliment Attired to defy, Impertinence subordinate At times to Majesty. Of Sentiments seditious Amenable to Law -- As Heresies of Transport Or Puck's Apostacy.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dExtrinsic to Attention Too intimate with Joy -- He compliments existence}
