my Horses The need is not of me --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1286\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI thought that nature was enough Till Human nature came But that the other did absorb As Parallax a Flame --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOf Human nature just aware There added the Divine Brief struggle for capacity The power to contain\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIs always as the contents But give a Giant room And you will lodge a Giant And not a smaller man In this short Life That only lasts an hour How much -- how little -- is Within our power\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1288\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLain in Nature -- so suffice us The enchantless Pod When we advertise existence For the missing Seed --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMaddest Heart that God created Cannot move a sod Pasted by the simple summer On the Longed for Dead\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1289\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLeft in immortal Youth On that low Plain That hath nor Retrospection Nor Again -- Ransomed from years -- Sequestered from Decay Canceled like Dawn In comprehensive Day --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1290\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe most pathetic thing I do Is play I hear from you -- I make believe until my Heart Almost believes it too But when I break it with the news You knew it was not true I wish I had not broken it -- Goliah -- so would you --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1291\u13\'0d\u13\'0dUntil the Desert knows That Water grows His Sands suffice But let him once suspect That Caspian Fact Sahara dies\u13\'0d\u13\'0dUtmost is relative -- Have not or Have Adjacent sums Enough -- the first Abode On the familiar Road Galloped in Dreams --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1292\u13\'0d\u13\'0dYesterday is History, 'Tis so far away -- Yesterday is Poetry -- 'Tis Philosophy --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dYesterday is mystery -- Where it is Today While we shrewdly speculate Flutter both away\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1293\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe things we thought that we should do We other things have done But those peculiar industries Have never been begun --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Lands we thought that we should seek When large enough to run By Speculation ceded To Speculation's Son --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Heaven, in which we hoped to pause When Discipline was done Untenable to Logic But possibly the one --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1294\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOf Life to own -- From Life to draw -- But never tough the reservoir --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1295\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTwo Lengths has every Day -- Its absolute extent And Area superior By Hope or Horror lent --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dEternity will be Velocity or Pause At Fundamental Signals From Fundamental Laws.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo die is not to go -- On Doom's consummate Chart No Territory new is staked -- Remain thou as thou art.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1296 Death's Waylaying not the sharpest Of the thefts of Time -- There Marauds a sorer Robber, Silence -- is his name -- No Assault, nor any Menace Doth betoken him. But from Life's consummate Cluster -- He supplants the Balm.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1297\u13\'0d\u13\'0dGo slow, my soul, to feed thyself Upon his rare approach -- Go rapid, lest Competing Death Prevail upon the Coach -- Go timid, should his final eye Determine thee amiss -- Go boldly -- for thou paid'st his price Redemption -- for a Kiss --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1298\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Mushroom is the Elf of Plants -At Evening, it is not -- At Morning, in a Truffled Hut It stop upon a Spot\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAs if it tarried always And yet its whole Career Is shorter than a Snake's Delay And fleeter than a Tare --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Tis Vegetation's Juggler -- The Germ of Alibi -- Doth like a Bubble antedate And like a Bubble, hie -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI feel as if the Grass was pleased To have it intermit -- This surreptitious scion Of Summer's circumspect.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHad Nature any supple Face Or could she one contemn -- Had Nature an Apostate -- That Mushroom -- it is Him!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1299\u13\'0d\u13\'0dDelight's Despair at setting Is that Delight is less Than the sufficing Longing That so impoverish.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dEnchantment's Perihelion Mistaken oft has been For the Authentic orbit Of its Anterior Sun.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dPoems No. 1300-1399\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1300\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFrom his slim Palace in the Dust He relegates the Realm, More loyal for the exody That has befallen him.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1301\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI cannot want it more -- I cannot want it less -- My Human Nature's fullest force Expends itself on this.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd yet it nothing is To him who easy owns -- Is Worth itself or Distance He fathoms who obtains.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1302\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI think that the Root of the Wind is Water -- It would not sound so deep Were it a Firmamental Product -- Airs no Oceans keep - Mediterranean intonations -- To a Current's Ear -- There is a maritime conviction In the Atmosphere --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1303\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNot One by Heaven defrauded stay -- Although he seem to steal He restitutes in some sweet way Secreted in his will -- 1304\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNot with a Club, the Heart is broken Nor with a Stone -- A Whip so small you could not see it I've known\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo lash the Magic Creature Till it fell, Yet that Whip's Name Too noble then to tell.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMagnanimous as Bird By Boy descried -- Singing unto the Stone Of which it died --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dShame need not crouch In such an Earth as Ours -- Shame -- stand erect -The Universe is yours.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1305\u13\'0d\u13\'0dRecollect the Face of me When in thy Felicity, Due in Paradise today Guest of mine assuredly --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOther Courtesies have been -- Other Courtesy may be -- We commend ourselves to thee Paragon of Chivalry.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1306\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSurprise is like a thrilling -- pungent -- Upon a tasteless meat Alone -- too acrid -- but combined An edible Delight.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1307\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThat short -- potential stir That each can make but once -- That Bustle so illustrious 'Tis almost Consequence --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIs the eclat of Death -- Oh, thou unknown Renown That not a Beggar would accept Had he the power to spurn --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1308\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Day she goes Or Day she stays Are equally supreme -- Existence has a stated width Departed, or at Home --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1309\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Infinite a sudden Guest Has been assumed to be -- But how can that stupendous come Which never went away?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1310\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Notice that is called the Spring Is but a month from here -- Put up my Heart thy Hoary work And take a Rosy Chair. Not any House the Flowers keep -The Birds enamor Care -- Our salary the longest Day Is nothing but a Bier.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1311\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThis dirty -- little -- Heart Is freely mine. I won it with a Bun -- A Freckled shrine --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut eligibly fair To him who sees The Visage of the Soul And not the knees.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1312\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo break so vast a Heart Required a Blow as vast -- No Zephyr felled this Cedar straight -- 'Twas undeserved Blast --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1313\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWarm in her Hand these accents lie While faithful and afar The Grace so awkward for her sake Its fond subjection wear --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1314\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhen a Lover is a Beggar Abject is his Knee -- When a Lover is an Owner Different is he --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhat he begged is then the Beggar -- Oh disparity -- Bread of Heaven resents bestowal Like an obloquy --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1315\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhich is the best -- the Moon or the Crescent? Neither -- said the Moon -- That is best which is not -- Achieve it -- You efface the Sheen.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNot of detention is Fruition -- Shudder to attain. Transport's decomposition follows -He is Prism born.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1316\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWinter is good -- his Hoar Delights Italic flavor yield To Intellects inebriate With Summer, or the World --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dGeneric as a Quarry And hearty -- as a Rose -- Invited with Asperity But welcome when he goes.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1317\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAbraham to kill him -- Was distinctly told -- Isaac was an Urchin -- Abraham was old --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNot a hesitation -- Abraham complied -- Flattered by Obeisance Tyranny demurred --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIsaac -- to his children Lived to tell the tale -- Moral -- with a Mastiff Manners may prevail.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1318\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFrigid and sweet Her parting Face -Frigid and fleet my Feet -- Alien and vain whatever Clime Acrid whatever Fate.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dGiven to me without the Suit Riches and Name and Realm -- Who was She to withhold from me Penury and Home?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1319\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHow News must feel when travelling If News have any Heart Alighting at the Dwelling 'Twill enter like a Dart!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhat News must think when pondering If News have any Thought Concerning the stupendousness Of its perceiveless freight!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhat News will do when every Man Shall comprehend as one And not in all the Universe A thing to tell remain?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1320 Dear March -- Come in -- How glad I am -- I hoped for you before --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dPut down your Hat -- You must have walked -- How out of Breath you are -- Dear March, Come right up the stairs with me -- I have so much to tell -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI got your Letter, and the Birds -- The Maples never knew that you were coming -- till I called I declare -- how Red their Faces grew -- But March, forgive me -- and All those Hills you left for me to Hue -- There was no Purple suitable -- You took it all with you --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWho knocks? That April. Lock the Door -- I will not be pursued -- He stayed away a Year to call When I am occupied - But trifles look so trivial As soon as you have come\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThat Blame is just}
