man Life But in a Squirrel's estimate A Saucer hold a Loaf.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Table of a Tree Demands the little King And every Breeze that run along His Dining Room do swing.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHis Cutlery -- he keeps Within his Russer Lips -- To see it flashing when he dines Do Birmingham eclipse -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dConvicted -- could we be Of our Minutiae The smallest Citizen that flies Is heartier than we -- 1375\u13\'0d\u13\'0dDeath warrants are supposed to be An enginery of equity A merciful mistake A pencil in an Idol's Hand A Devotee has oft consigned To Crucifix or Block\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1376\u13\'0d\u13\'0dDreams are the subtle Dower That make us rich an Hour -- Then fling us poor Out of the purple Door Into the Precinct raw Possessed before --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1377\u13\'0d\u13\'0dForbidden Fruit a flavor has That lawful Orchards mocks -- How luscious lies within the Pod The Pea that Duty locks --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1378\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHis Heart was darker than the starless night For that there is a morn But in this black Receptacle Can be no Bode of Dawn\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1379\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHis Mansion in the Pool The Frog forsakes -- He rises on a Log And statements makes -- His Auditors two Worlds Deducting me -- The Orator of April Is hoarse Today -- His Mittens at his Feet No Hand hath he -- His eloquence a Bubble As Fame should be -- Applaud him to discover To your chagrin Demosthenes has vanished In Waters Green --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1380\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHow much the present moment means To those who've nothing more -- The Fop -- the Carp -- the Atheist -Stake an entire store Upon a Moment's shallow Rim While their commuted Feet The Torrents of Eternity Do all but inundate --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1381\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI suppose the time will come Aid it in the coming When the Bird will crowd the Tree And the Bee be booming.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI suppose the time will come Hinder it a little When the Corn in Silk will dress And in Chintz the Apple\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI believe the Day will be When the Jay will giggle At his new white House the Earth That, too, halt a little --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1382\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIn many and reportless places We feel a Joy -- Reportless, also, but sincere as Nature Or Deity --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt comes, without a consternation -- Dissolves -- the same -- But leaves a sumptuous Destitution -Without a Name --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dProfane it by a search -- we cannot It has no home -- Nor we who having once inhaled it -Thereafter roam.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1383\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLong Years apart -- can make no Breach a second cannot fill -- The absence of the Witch does not Invalidate the spell --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe embers of a Thousand Years Uncovered by the Hand That fondled them when they were Fire Will stir and understand --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1384\u13\'0d\u13\'0dPraise it -- 'tis dead -- It cannot glow -- Warm this inclement Ear With the encomium it earned Since it was gathered here -- Invest this alabaster Zest In the Delights of Dust -Remitted -- since it flitted it In recusance august.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1385\u13\'0d\u13\'0d"Secrets" is a daily word Yet does not exist -- Muffled -- it remits surmise -- Murmured -- it has ceased -- Dungeoned in the Human Breast Doubtless secrets lie - But that Grate inviolate - Goes nor comes away Nothing with a Tongue or Ear -- Secrets stapled there Will emerge but once -- and dumb -- To the Sepulchre --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1386\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSummer -- we all have seen -- A few of us -- believed -- A few -- the more aspiring Unquestionably loved --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut Summer does not care -- She goes her spacious way As eligible as the moon To our Temerity --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Doom to be adored -- The Affluence conferred -- Unknown as to an Ecstasy The Embryo endowed -- 1387\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Butterfly's Numidian Gown With spots of Burnish roasted on Is proof against the Sun Yet prone to shut its spotted Fan And panting on a Clover lean As if it were undone --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1388\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThose cattle smaller than a Bee That herd upon the eye -- Whose tillage is the passing Crumb -- Those Cattle are the Fly -- Of Barns for Winter -- blameless -- Extemporaneous stalls They found to our objection -- On eligible walls -- Reserving the presumption To suddenly descend And gallop on the Furniture -- Or odiouser offend -- Of their peculiar calling Unqualified to judge To Nature we remand them To justify or scourge --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1389\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTouch lightly Nature's sweet Guitar Unless thou know'st the Tune Or every Bird will point at thee Because a Bard too soon --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1390\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThese held their Wick above the West -- Till when the Red declined -- Or how the Amber aided it -- Defied to be defined --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThen waned without disparagement In a dissembling Hue That would not let the Eye decide Did it abide or no --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1391\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThey might not need me -- yet they might -- I'll let my Heart be just in sight -- A smile so small as mine might be Precisely their necessity --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1392\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHope is a strange invention -- A Patent of the Heart -- In unremitting action Yet never wearing out -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOf this electric Adjunct Not anything is known But its unique momentum Embellish all we own --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1393\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLay this Laurel on the One Too intrinsic for Renown -- Laurel -- veil your deathless tree -- Him you chasten, that is He!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1394 Whose Pink career may have a close Portentous as our own, who knows? To imitate these Neighbors fleet In awe and innocence, were meet.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1395\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAfter all Birds have been investigated and laid aside -- Nature imparts the little Blue-Bird -- assured Her conscientious Voice will soar unmoved Above ostensible Vicissitude.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFirst at the March -- competing with the Wind -Her panting note exalts us -- like a friend -- Last to adhere when Summer cleaves away -- Elegy of Integrity.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1396\u13\'0d\u13\'0dShe laid her docile Crescent down And this confiding Stone Still states to Dates that have forgot The News that she is gone --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSo constant to its stolid trust, The Shaft that never knew -- It shames the Constancy that fled Before its emblem flew --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1397\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt sounded as if the Streets were running And then -- the Streets stood still -- Eclipse -- was all we could see at the Window And Awe -- was all we could feel.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBy and by -- the boldest stole out of his Covert To see if Time was there -- Nature was in an Opal Apron, Mixing fresher Air.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1398\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI have no Life but this -To lead it here -- Nor any Death -- but lest Dispelled from there --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNor tie to Earths to come -- Nor Action new -- Except through this extent -- The Realm of you --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1399\u13\'0d\u13\'0dPerhaps they do not go so far As we who stay, suppose -- Perhaps come closer, for the lapse Of their corporeal clothes --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt may be know so certainly How short we have to fear That comprehension antedates And estimates us there -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dPoems No. 1400-1499\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1400\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhat mystery pervades a well! That water lives so far -- A neighbor from another world Residing in a jar\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhose limit none have ever seen, But just his lid of glass - Like looking every time you please In an abyss's face!\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe grass does not appear afraid, I often wonder he Can stand so close and look so bold At what is awe to me.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dRelated somehow they may be, The sedge stands next the sea -- Where he is floorless And does no timidity betray\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut nature is a stranger yet; The ones that cite her most Have never passed her haunted house, Nor simplified her ghost.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo pity those that know her not Is helped by the regret That those who know her, know her less The nearer her they get.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1401\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo own a Susan of my own Is of itself a Bliss -- Whatever Realm I forfeit, Lord, Continue me in this! 1402\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo the stanch Dust We safe commit thee -- Tongue if it hath, Inviolate to thee -- Silence -- denote -- And Sanctity -- enforce thee -- Passenger -- of Infinity --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1403\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMy Maker -- let me be Enamored most of thee -- But nearer this I more should miss --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1404\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMarch is the Month of Expectation. The things we do not know -- The Persons of prognostication Are coming now -- We try to show becoming firmness -- But pompous Joy Betrays us, as his first Betrothal Betrays a Boy.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1405\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBees are Black, with Gilt Surcingles -- Buccaneers of Buzz. Ride abroad in ostentation And subsist on Fuzz.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFuzz ordained -- not Fuzz contingent -- Marrows of the Hill. Jugs -- a Universe's fracture Could not jar or spill.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1406\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNo Passenger was known to flee -- That lodged a night in memory -- That wily -- subterranean Inn Contrives that none go out again --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1407\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Field of Stubble, lying sere Beneath the second Sun -- Its Toils to Brindled People thrust -Its Triumphs -- to the Bin -- Accosted by a timid Bird Irresolute of Alms -- Is often seen -- but seldom felt, On our New England Farms --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1408\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Fact that Earth is Heaven}
