-- Whether Heaven is Heaven or not If not an Affidavit Of that specific Spot Not only must confirm us That it is not for us But that it would affront us To dwell in such a place --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1409 Could mortal lip divine The undeveloped Freight Of a delivered syllable 'Twould crumble with the weight.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1410\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI shall not murmur if at last The ones I loved below Permission have to understand For what I shunned them so -- Divulging it would rest my Heart But it would ravage theirs -- Why, Katie, Treason has a Voice -- But mine -- dispels -- in Tears.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1411\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOf Paradise' existence All we know Is the uncertain certainty -- But its vicinity infer, By its Bisecting Messenger --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1412\u13\'0d\u13\'0dShame is the shawl of Pink In which we wrap the Soul To keep it from infesting Eyes -- The elemental Veil Which helpless Nature drops When pushed upon a scene Repugnant to her probity -- Shame is the tint divine. Sweet Skepticism of the Heart -- That knows -- and does not know -- And tosses like a Fleet of Balm -- Affronted by the snow -- Invites and then retards the Truth Lest Certainty be sere Compared with the delicious throe Of transport thrilled with Fear --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1414\u13\'0d\u13\'0dUnworthy of her Breast Though by that scathing test What Soul survive? By her exacting light How counterfeit the white We chiefly have!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1415\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA wild Blue sky abreast of Winds That threatened it -- did run And crouched behind his Yellow Door Was the defiant sun -- Some conflict with those upper friends So genial in the main That we deplore peculiarly Their arrogant campaign --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1416\u13\'0d\u13\'0dCrisis is sweet and yet the Heart Upon the hither side Has Dowers of Prospective To Denizens denied Inquire of the closing Rose Which rapture she preferred And she will point you sighing To her rescinded Bud.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1417\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHow Human Nature dotes On what it can't detect. The moment that a Plot is plumbed Prospective is extinct -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dProspective is the friend Reserved for us to know When Constancy is clarified Of Curiosity --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOf subjects that resist Redoubtablest is this Where go we -- Go we anywhere Creation after this?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1418\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHow lonesome the Wind must feel Nights -- When people have put out the Lights And everything that has an Inn Closes the shutter and goes in --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHow pompous the Wind must feel Noons Stepping to incorporeal Tunes Correcting errors of the sky And clarifying scenery\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHow mighty the Wind must feel Morns Encamping on a thousand dawns Espousing each and spurning all Then soaring to his Temple Tall -- It was a quiet seeming Day -- There was no harm in earth or sky -- Till with the closing sun There strayed an accidental Red A Strolling Hue, one would have said To westward of the Town --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut when the Earth began to jar And Houses vanished with a roar And Human Nature hid We comprehended by the Awe As those that Dissolution saw The Poppy in the Cloud\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1420\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOne Joy of so much anguish Sweet nature has for me I shun it as I do Despair Or dear iniquity -- Why Birds, a Summer morning Before the Quick of Day Should stab my ravished spirit With Dirks of Melody Is part of an inquiry That will receive reply When Flesh and Spirit sunder In Death's Immediately --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1421\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSuch are the inlets of the mind -- His outlets -- would you see Ascend with me the eminence Of immortality -- Summer has two Beginnings -- Beginning once in June -- Beginning in October Affectingly again --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWithout, perhaps, the Riot But graphicker for Grace -- As finer is a going Than a remaining Face --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dDeparting then -- forever -- Forever -- until May -- Forever is deciduous Except to those who die --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1423\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe fairest Home I ever knew Was founded in an Hour By Parties also that I knew A spider and a Flower -- A manse of mechlin and of Floes --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1424\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Gentian has a parched Corolla -- Like azure dried 'Tis Nature's buoyant juices Beatified - Without a vaunt or sheen As casual as Rain And as benign --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhen most is part -- it comes -- Nor isolate it seems Its Bond its Friend -- To fill its Fringed career And aid an aged Year Abundant end --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIts lot -- were it forgot -This Truth endear -- Fidelity is gain Creation is o'er --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1425\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe inundation of the Spring Enlarges every soul -- It sweeps the tenement away But leaves the Water whole --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIn which the soul at first estranged -Seeks faintly for its shore But acclimated -- pines no more For that Peninsula --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1426\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe pretty Rain from those sweet Eaves Her unintending Eyes -- Took her own Heart, including ours, By innocent Surprise --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe wrestle in her simple Throat To hold the feeling down That vanquished her -- defeated Feat -- Was Fervor's sudden Crown --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1427\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo earn it by disdaining it Is Fame's consummate Fee -- He loves what spurns him -- Look behind -- He is pursuing thee. So let us gather -- every Day -- The Aggregate of Life's Bouquet Be Honor and not shame --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1428\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWater makes many Beds For those averse to sleep -- Its awful chamber open stands -- Its Curtains blandly sweep -- Abhorrent is the Rest In undulating Rooms Whose Amplitude no end invades -- Whose Axis never comes.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1429\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWe shun because we prize her Face Lest sight's ineffable disgrace Our Adoration stain\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1430\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWho never wanted -- maddest Joy Remains to him unknown -- The Banquet of Abstemiousness Defaces that of Wine -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWithin its reach, though yet ungrasped Desire's perfect Goal -- No nearer -- lest the Actual -- Should disentrall thy soul --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1431 With Pinions of Disdain The soul can farther fly Than any feather specified in Ornithology -- It wafts this sordid Flesh Beyond its dull -- control And during its electric gale -- The body is a soul -- instructing by the same -- How little work it be -- To put off filaments like this for immortality\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1432\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSpurn the temerity -- Rashness of Calvary -- Gay were Gethsemane Knew we of Thee --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1433\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHow brittle are the Piers On which our Faith doth tread -- No Bridge below doth totter so -- Yet none hath such a Crowd.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt is as old as God -- Indeed -- 'twas built by him -- He sent his Son to test the Plank, And he pronounced it firm.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1434\u13\'0d\u13\'0dGo not too near a House of Rose -- The depredation of a Breeze -- Or inundation of a Dew Alarms its walls away --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNor try to tie the Butterfly, Nor climb the Bars of Ecstasy, In insecurity to lie Is Joy's insuring quality.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1435\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNot that he goes -- we love him more Who led us while he stayed. Beyond earth's trafficking frontier, For what he moved, he made.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1436\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThan Heaven more remote, For Heaven is the root, But these the flitted seed. More flown indeed Than ones that never were, Or those that hide, and are.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhat madness, by their side, A vision to provide Of future days They cannot praise.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMy soul, to find them, come, They cannot call, they're dumb, Nor prove, nor woo, But that they have abode Is absolute as God, And instant, too.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1437\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Dew sufficed itself -- And satisfied a Leaf And felt "how vast a destiny" -- "How trivial is Life!" The Sun went out to work -- The Day went out to play And not again that Dew be seen By Physiognomy\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhether by Day Abducted Or emptied by the Sun Into the Sea in passing Eternally unknown\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAttested to this Day That awful Tragedy By Transport's instability And Doom's celerity.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1438\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBehold this little Bane -The Boon of all alive -- As common as it is unknown The name of it is Love -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo lack of it is Woe -- To own of it is Wound - Not elsewhere -- if in Paradise Its Tantamount be found --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1439\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHow ruthless are the gentle -- How cruel are the kind - God broke his contract to his Lamb To qualify the Wind --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1440\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe healed Heart shows its shallow scar With confidential moan -- Not mended by Mortality Are Fabrics truly torn -- To go its convalescent way So shameless is to see More genuine were Perfidy Than such Fidelity.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1441\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThese Fevered Days -- to take them to the Forest Where Waters cool around the mosses crawl -- And shade is all that devastates the stillness Seems it sometimes this would be all --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1442\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo mend each tattered Faith There is a needle fair Though no appearance indicate -- 'Tis threaded in the Air -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAnd though it do not wear As if it never Tore 'Tis very comfortable indeed And spacious as before -\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1443\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA chilly Peace infests the Grass The Sun respectful lies - Not any Trance of industry These shadows scrutinize --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhose Allies go no more astray For service or for Glee -- But all mankind deliver here From whatsoever sea -- A little Snow was here and there Disseminated in her Hair -- Since she and I had met and played Decade had gathered to Decade --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut Time had added not obtained Impregnable the Rose For summer too indelible Too obdurate for Snows --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1445\u13\'0d\u13\'0dDeath is the supple Suitor That wins at last -- It is a stealthy Wooing Conducted first By pallid innuendoes And dim approach But brave at last with Bugles And a bisected Coach It bears away in triumph To Troth unknown And Kindred as responsive As Porcelain.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1446\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHis Mind like Fabrics of the East Displayed to the despair Of everyone but here and there An humble Purchaser -- For though his price was not of Gold -- More arduous there is - That one should comprehend the worth Was all the price there was -- How good his Lava Bed, To this laborious Boy -- Who must be up to call the World And dress the sleepy Day --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1448\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHow soft a Caterpillar steps -- I fond one on my Hand From such a velvet world it comes Such plushes at command Its soundless travels just arrest My slow -- terrestrial eye Intent upon its own career What use has it for me --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1449\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI thought the Train would never come -- How slow the whistle sang -- I don't believe a peevish Bird So whimpered for the Spring -- I taught my Heart a hundred times Precisely what to say -- Provoking Lover, when you came Its Treatise flew away To hide my strategy too late To wiser be too soon - For miseries so halcyon The happiness atone --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1450\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Road was lit with Moon and star -- The Trees were bright and still -- Descried I -- by the distant Light A Traveller}
