pher -- As long as he can blush Perdition is Opprobrium -- Past that, he sins in peace --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1461\u13\'0d\u13\'0d"Heavenly Father" -- take to thee The supreme iniquity Fashioned by thy candid Hand In a moment contraband -- Though to trust us -- seems to us More respectful -- "We are Dust" -- We apologize to thee For thine own Duplicity -- We knew not that we were to live -- Nor when -- we are to die -- Our ignorance -- our cuirass is -- We wear Mortality As lightly as an Option Gown Till asked to take it off - By his intrusion, God is known -- It is the same with Life -\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1463\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Route of Evanescence With a revolving Wheel -- A Resonance of Emerald -- A Rush of Cochineal -- And every Blossom on the Bush Adjusts its tumbled Head -- The mail from Tunis, probably, An easy Morning's Ride --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1464\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOne thing of it we borrow And promise to return -- The Booty and the Sorrow Its Sweetness to have known -- One thing of it we covet -- The power to forget -- The Anguish of the Avarice Defrays the Dross of it -\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1465 Before you thought of Spring Except as a Surmise You see -- God bless his suddenness -- A Fellow in the Skies Of independent Hues A little weather worn Inspiriting habiliments Of Indigo and Brown -- With specimens of Song As if for you to choose - Discretion in the interval With gay delays he goes To some superior Tree Without a single Leaf And shouts for joy to Nobody But his seraphic self --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1466\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOne of the ones that Midas touched Who failed to touch us all Was that confiding Prodigal The reeling Oriole --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSo drunk he disavows it With badinage divine -- So dazzling we mistake him For an alighting Mine --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Pleader -- a Dissembler -- An Epicure -- a Thief -- Betimes an Oratorio -- An Ecstasy in chief --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Jesuit of Orchards He cheats as he enchants Of an entire Attar For his decamping wants --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe splendor of a Burmah The Meteor of Birds, Departing like a Pageant Of Ballads and of Bards --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI never thought that Jason sought For any Golden Fleece But then I am a rural man With thoughts that make for Peace --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBut if there were a Jason, Tradition bear with me Behold his lost Aggrandizement Upon the Apple Tree --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1467\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA little overflowing word That any, hearing, had inferred For Ardor or for Tears, Though Generations pass away, Traditions ripen and decay, As eloquent appears --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1468\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA winged spark doth soar about -- I never met it near For Lightning it is oft mistook When nights are hot and sere --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIts twinkling Travels it pursues Above the Haunts of men -- A speck of Rapture -- first perceived By feeling it is gone -- Rekindled by some action quaint\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1469\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIf wrecked upon the Shoal of Thought How is it with the Sea? The only Vessel that is shunned Is safe -- Simplicity -- 1470\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Sweets of Pillage, can be known To no one but the Thief -- Compassion for Integrity Is his divinest Grief --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1471\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTheir Barricade against the Sky The martial Trees withdraw And with a Flag at every turn Their Armies are no more.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhat Russet Halts in Nature's March They indicate or cause An inference of Mexico Effaces the Surmise --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dRecurrent to the After Mind That Massacre of Air -- The Wound that was not Wound nor Scar But Holidays of War\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1472\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo see the Summer Sky Is Poetry, though never in a Book it lie -- True Poems flee --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1473\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWe talked with each other about each other Though neither of us spoke -- We were listening to the seconds' Races And the Hoofs of the Clock -- Pausing in Front of our Palsied Faces Time compassion took - Arks of Reprieve he offered to us -- Ararats -- we took --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1474\u13\'0d\u13\'0dEstranged from Beauty -- none can be -- For Beauty is Infinity -- And power to be finite ceased Before Identity was leased.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1475\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFame is the one that does not stay -- Its occupant must die Or out of sight of estimate Ascend incessantly -- Or be that most insolvent thing A Lightning in the Germ -- Electrical the embryo But we demand the Flame\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1476\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHis voice decrepit was with Joy -- Her words did totter so How old the News of Love must be To make Lips elderly That purled a moment since with Glee -- Is it Delight or Woe -- Or Terror -- that do decorate This livid interview --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1477 How destitute is he Whose Gold is firm Who finds it every time The small stale Sum -- When Love with but a Pence Will so display As is a disrespect To India.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1478\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLook back on Time, with kindly eyes -- He doubtless did his best -- How softly sinks that trembling sun In Human Nature's West --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1479\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Devil -- had he fidelity Would be the best friend -- Because he has ability -But Devils cannot mend -- Perfidy is the virtue That would but he resign The Devil -- without question Were thoroughly divine\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1480\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe fascinating chill that music leaves Is Earth's corroboration Of Ecstasy's impediment -- 'Tis Rapture's germination In timid and tumultuous soil A fine -- estranging creature -- To something upper wooing us But not to our Creator -- 1481\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe way Hope builds his House It is not with a sill -- Nor Rafter -- has that Edifice But only Pinnacle --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAbode in as supreme This superficies As if it were of Ledges smit Or mortised with the Laws --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1482\u13\'0d\u13\'0d'Tis whiter than an Indian Pipe -- 'Tis dimmer than a Lace -- No stature has it, like a Fog When you approach the place -- Nor any voice imply it here Or intimate it there A spirit -- how doth it accost -- What function hat the Air? This limitless Hyperbole Each one of us shall be -- 'Tis Drama -- if Hypothesis It be not Tragedy --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1483\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Robin is a Gabriel In humble circumstances -- His Dress denotes him socially, Of Transport's Working Classes -- He has the punctuality Of the New England Farmer -- The same oblique integrity, A Vista vastly warmer -\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA small but sturdy Residence A self denying Household, The Guests of Perspicacity Are all that cross his Threshold -- As covert as a Fugitive, Cajoling Consternation By Ditties to the Enemy And Sylvan Punctuation --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1484\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWe shall find the Cube of the Rainbow. Of that, there is no doubt. But the Arc of a Lover's conjecture Eludes the finding out.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1485\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLove is done when Love's begun, Sages say, But have Sages known? Truth adjourn your Boon Without Day.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1486\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHer spirit rose to such a height Her countenance it did inflate Like one that fed on awe. More prudent to assault the dawn Than merit the ethereal scorn That effervesced from her.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1487\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Savior must have been A docile Gentleman -- To come so far so cold a Day For little Fellowmen --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Road to Bethlehem Since He and I were Boys Was leveled, but for that 'twould be A rugged billion Miles --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1488\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBirthday of but a single pang That there are less to come -- Afflictive is the Adjective But affluent the doom --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1489\u13\'0d\u13\'0dA Dimple in the Tomb Makes that ferocious Room A Home --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1490\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Face in evanescence lain Is more distinct than ours -- And ours surrendered for its sake As Capsules are for Flower's -- Or is it the confiding sheen Dissenting to enamor us Of Detriment divine?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1491\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Road to Paradise is plain, And holds scarce one. Not that it is not firm But we presume A Dimpled Road Is more preferred. The Belles of Paradise are few -- Not me -- nor you -- But unsuspected things - Mines have no Wings.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1492\u13\'0d\u13\'0d"And with what body do they come?" -- Then they do come -- Rejoice! What Door -- What Hour -- Run -- run -- My Soul! Illuminate the House!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d"Body!" Then real -- a Face and Eyes -- To know that it is them! Paul knew the Man that knew the News -- He passed through Bethlehem --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1493\u13\'0d\u13\'0dCould that sweet Darkness where they dwell Be once disclosed to us The clamor for their loveliness Would burst the Loneliness --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1494 The competitions of the sky Corrodeless ply. 1495\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Thrill came slowly like a Boom for Centuries delayed Its fitness growing like the Flood In sumptuous solitude -- The desolations only missed While Rapture changed its Dress And stood amazed before the Change In ravished Holiness --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1496\u13\'0d\u13\'0dAll that I do Is in review To his enamored mind I know his eye Where e'er I ply Is pushing close behind Not any Port Nor any flight But he doth there preside What omnipresence lies in wait For her to be a Bride\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1497\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFacts by our side are never sudden Until they}
