-- the Troubador -- Sin -- a distinguished Precipice Others must resist -- Boys that "believe" are very lonesome -- Other Boys are "lost" - Had but the Tale a warbling Teller -All the Boys would come -- Orpheus' Sermon captivated -- It did not condemn --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1546\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSweet Pirate of the heart, Not Pirate of the Sea, What wrecketh thee? Some spice's Mutiny -- Some Attar's perfidy? Confide in me.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1547\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHope is a subtle Glutton -- He feeds upon the Fair -And yet -- inspected closely What Abstinence is there --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHis is the Halcyon Table -- That never seats but One -- And whatsoever is consumed The same amount remain --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1548\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMeeting by Accident, We hovered by design -- As often as a Century An error so divine Is ratified by Destiny, But Destiny is old And economical of Bliss As Midas is of Gold --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1549\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMy Wars are laid away in Books -- I have one Battle more -- A Foe whom I have never seen But oft has scanned me o'er -- And hesitated me between And others at my side, But chose the best -- Neglecting me -- till All the rest, have died -- How sweet if I am not forgot By Chums that passed away -- Since Playmates at threescore and ten Are such a scarcity --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1550\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe pattern of the sun Can fit but him alone For sheen must have a Disk To be a sun --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1551\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThose -- dying then, Knew where they went -- They went to God's Right Hand -- That Hand is amputated now And God cannot be found --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe abdication of Belief Makes the Behavior small -- Better an ignis fatuus Than no illume at all --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1552\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWithin thy Grave! Oh no, but on some other flight -- Thou only camest to mankind To rend it with Good night --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1553\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBliss is the plaything of the child -- The secret of the man The sacred stealth of Boy and Girl Rebuke it if we can "Go tell it" -- What a Message -- To whom -- is specified - Not murmur -- not endearment -- But simply -- we -- obeyed -- Obeyed -- a Lure -- a Longing? Oh Nature -- none of this -- To Law -- said sweet Thermopylae I give my dying Kiss --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1555\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI groped for him before I knew With solemn nameless need All other bounty sudden chaff For this foreshadowed Food Which others taste and spurn and sneer -- Though I within suppose That consecrated it could be The only Food that grows\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1556\u13\'0d\u13\'0dImage of Light, Adieu -- Thanks for the interview -- So long -- so short -- Preceptor of the whole -- Coeval Cardinal -- Impart -- Depart --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1557\u13\'0d\u13\'0dLives he in any other world My faith cannot reply Before it was imperative 'Twas all distinct to me -- Of Death I try to think like this -- The Well in which they lay us Is but the Likeness of the Brook That menaced not to slay us, But to invite by that Dismay Which is the Zest of sweetness To the same Flower Hesperian, Decoying but to greet us --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dI do remember when a Child With bolder Playmates straying To where a Brook that seemed a Sea Withheld us by its roaring From just the Purple Flower beyond Until constrained to clutch it If Doom itself were the result, The boldest leaped, and clutched it -\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1559\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTried always and Condemned by thee Permit me this reprieve That dying I may earn the look For which I cease to live --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1560\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo be forgot by thee Surpasses Memory Of other minds The Heart cannot forget Unless it contemplate What it declines I was regarded then Raised from oblivion A single time To be remembered what -- Worthy to be forgot Is my renown\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1561\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNo Brigadier throughout the Year So civic as the Jay -- A Neighbor and a Warrior too With shrill felicity Pursuing Winds that censure us A February Day, The Brother of the Universe Was never blown away -- The Snow and he are intimate -- I've often seem them play When Heaven looked upon us all With such severity I felt apology were due To an insulted sky Whose pompous frown was Nutriment To their Temerity -- The Pillow of this daring Head Is pungent Evergreens -- His Larder -- terse and Militant -- Unknown -- refreshing things -- His Character -- a Tonic -- His future -- a Dispute -- Unfair an Immortality That leaves this Neighbor out --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1562\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHer Losses make our Gains ashamed -- She bore Life's empty Pack As gallantly as if the East Were swinging at her Back. Life's empty Pack is heaviest, As every Porter knows -- In vain to punish Honey -- It only sweeter grows. By homely gift and hindered Words The human heart is told Of Nothing -- "Nothing" is the force That renovates the World --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1564\u13\'0d\u13\'0dPass to they Rendezvous of Light, Pangless except for us - Who slowly for the Mystery Which thou hast leaped across!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1565\u13\'0d\u13\'0dSome Arrows slay but whom they strike -- But this slew all but him -- Who so appareled his Escape -- Too trackless for a Tomb --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1566\u13\'0d\u13\'0dClimbing to reach the costly Hearts To which he gave the worth, He broke them, fearing punishment He ran away from Earth --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1567\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Heart has many Doors -- I can but knock -- For any sweet "Come in" Impelled to hark -- Not saddened by repulse, Repast to me That somewhere, there exists, Supremacy --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1568\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo see her is a Picture - To hear her is a Tune - To know her an Intemperance As innocent as June -- To know her not -- Affliction -- To own her for a Friend A warmth as near as if the Sun Were shining in your Hand.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1569\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Clock strikes one that just struck two -- Some schism in the Sum -- A Vagabond for Genesis Has wrecked the Pendulum --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1570\u13\'0d\u13\'0dForever honored by the Tree Whose Apple Winterworn Enticed to Breakfast from the Sky Two Gabriels Yestermorn.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThey registered in Nature's Book As Robins -- Sire and Son -- But Angels have that modest way To screen them from Renown. How slow the Wind -- how slow the sea -- how late their Fathers be!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1572\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWe wear our sober Dresses when we die, But Summer, frilled as for a Holiday Adjourns her sigh --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1573\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo the bright east she flies, Brothers of Paradise Remit her home, Without a change of wings, Or Love's convenient things, Enticed to come.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dFashioning what she is, Fathoming what she was, We deem we dream -- And that dissolves the days Through which existence strays Homeless at home.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1574\u13\'0d\u13\'0dNo ladder needs the bird but skies To situate its wings, Nor any leader's grim baton Arraigns it as it sings. The implements of bliss are few -- As Jesus says of Him, "Come unto me" the moiety That wafts the cherubim. The Bat is dun, with wrinkled Wings -Like fallow Article -- And not a song pervade his Lips -- Or none perceptible.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHis small Umbrella quaintly halved Describing in the Air An Arc alike inscrutable Elate Philosopher.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dDeputed from what Firmament -- Of what Astute Abode -- Empowered with what Malignity Auspiciously withheld --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo his adroit Creator Acribe no less the praise -- Beneficent, believe me, His Eccentricities --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1576\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Spirit lasts -- but in what mode -- Below, the Body speaks, But as the Spirit furnishes -- Apart, it never talks -- The Music in the Violin Does not emerge alone But Arm in Arm with Touch, yet Touch Alone -- is not a Tune -- The Spirit lurks within the Flesh Like Tides within the Sea That make the Water live, estranged What would the Either be? Does that know -- now -- or does it cease -- That which to this is done, Resuming at a mutual date With every future one? Instinct pursues the Adamant, Exacting this Reply -- Adversity if it may be, or Wild Prosperity, The Rumor's Gate was shut so tight Before my Mind was sown, Not even a Prognostic's Push Could make a Dent thereon --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1577\u13\'0d\u13\'0dMorning is due to all -- To some -- the Night -- To an imperial few -- The Auroral light.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1578\u13\'0d\u13\'0dBlossoms will run away, Cakes reign but a Day, But Memory like Melody Is pink Eternally.\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1579\u13\'0d\u13\'0dIt would not know if it were spurned, This gallant little flower - How therefore safe to be a flower If one would tamper there.\u13\'0d\u13\'0dTo enter, it would not aspire -- But may it not despair That it is not a Cavalier, To dare and perish there? We shun it ere it comes, Afraid of Joy, Then sue it to delay And lest it fly, Beguile it more and more -- May not this be Old Suitor Heaven, Like our dismay at thee?\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1581\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe farthest Thunder that I heard Was nearer than the Sky And rumbles still, though torrid Noons Have lain their missiles by -- The Lightning that preceded it Struck no one but myself -- But I would not exchange the Bolt For all the rest of Life - Indebtedness to Oxygen The Happy may repay, But not the obligation To Electricity -- It founds the Homes and decks the Days And every clamor bright Is but the gleam concomitant Of that waylaying Light -- The Thought is quiet as a Flake -- A Crash without a Sound, How Life's reverberation Its Explanation found --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1582\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWhere Roses would not dare to go, What Heart would risk the way -- And so I send my Crimson Scouts To sound the Enemy -- 1583\u13\'0d\u13\'0dWitchcraft was hung, in History, But History and I Find all the Witchcraft that we need Around us, every Day --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1584\u13\'0d\u13\'0dExpanse cannot be lost -- Not Joy, but a Decree Is Deity -- His Scene, Infinity -- Whose rumor's Gate was shut so tight Before my Beam was sown, Not even a Prognostic's push Could make a Dent thereon --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe World that thou hast opened Shuts for thee, But not alone, We all have followed thee -- Escape more slowly To thy Tracts of Sheen -- The Tent is listening, But the Troops are gone!\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1585\u13\'0d\u13\'0dThe Bird her punctual music brings And lays it in its place - Its place is in the Human Heart And in the Heavenly Grace -- What respite from her thrilling toil Did Beauty ever take -- But Work might be electric Rest To those that Magic make -- To her derided Home A Weed of Summer came -- She did not know her station low Nor Ignominy's Name -- Bestowed a summer long Upon a frameless flower -- Then swept as lightly from disdain As Lady from her Bower --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dOf Bliss the Codes are few -- As Jesus cites of Him -- "Come unto me" the moiety That wafts the Seraphim --\u13\'0d\u13\'0d1587\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHe ate and drank the precious Words -- His Spirit grew robust -- He knew no more that he was poor, Nor that his frame was Dust --\u13\'0d\u13\'0dHe danced along the dingy Days And this Bequest}
